title: family meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 2) in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let meat loaf stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 regular or one deep dish pie crust.

title: easy fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, in a one-gallon jug or jar.
Use Kool-Aid flavor to match the color scheme you are using. Example:
Lime for green or strawberry for pink, etc.
Fill the jug the rest of the way with water.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale to the punch when ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, Karo, butter, vanilla and pecans in this order, mixing well after each addition. Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Recipe makes 1 pie.
Double recipe makes 3 medium pies or 2 large and 1 individual pie.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Crumble cake and use as your first layer.
Mix pudding as directed.
Use as second layer. Layer pineapple, then layer cherry filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: warp drive chocolate pie
directions: In small bowl, combine wafers and butter.
Mix and press into the bottom of a 10-inch pie plate or spring-form pan.
Place in freezer for 1 hour.
In blender, combine chocolate chips, yolks and Kahlua and set aside.
In small saucepan, heat cream until it just comes to a boil.
With blender on low speed, pour hot cream into chocolate mixture.
Blend on high for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into frozen pie shell and chill at least 3 hours.
Do not freeze!
Slice into small wedges and serve on paper doily with two fresh strawberries on each slice.

title: butterscotch bonbons
directions: In top of a double boiler, combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Melt over hot, not boiling, water, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix gently until well coated.
Spoon into tiny 1/2 ounce paper cups or drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill until set.
Makes 3 dozen dropped candies or 4 dozen in cups.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Press biscuits into pie pan.
Brown ground beef and then mix in other ingredients except for cheese. Pour into pie pan. Put cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry in skillet with oil.
Drop by large spoonfuls.
Mash down in skillet while frying.
Brown; turn over to other side.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, onions and carrots.
Spray baking dish with Pam and put in vegetables.
Lay the pork chops on top. Spread soup on top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: oriental haystack cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the chips over a low heat, stirring constantly until smooth (or microwave on High for 2 minutes). Remove immediately and stir in noodles.
Stir well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper covered baking sheets.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and make into balls. Chill 15 minutes. Brown balls in skillet.
Mix last 4 ingredients with drippings in skillet.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon jello party salad
directions: Mix jello and let it start to "set."
Add marshmallows to pineapple while jello sets, then add the pineapple to the jello and add the bananas.
After the jello has set for a short time, add Topping.

title: apple brownie squares
directions: Blend margarine, eggs and sugar well.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti sauce(crock-pot)
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and sausage; drain off fat. Transfer to an electric slow crockery cooker.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, Burgundy, olives, 1/3 cup water, bay leaves, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Cover crockery cooker and cook on high heat setting for 5 to 6 hours.
Blend 2 tablespoons cold water slowly into cornstarch; stir into tomato mixture.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: brown beef stew
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and brown in drippings.
Add water; cover and simmer until almost tender, 2 or 3 hours.
Add vegetables, season with salt and pepper and continue to simmer until vegetables are done.
Stir occasionally.

title: pepper and onion steak
directions: (I use 2 tablespoons teriyaki sauce in place of soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.)

title: cherry jubilee pie
directions: Combine pie filling, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside. Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on box except omit 2 tablespoons of milk.
Beat until stiff.
Add the 1/4 cup sugar at low speed; gently fold in sour cream.
Spoon 1/2 the cherry mixture into baked pie shell.
Spread 2/3 whipped topping mixture over cherries, then gently spoon the remaining cherries over whipped topping mixture.
With remaining topping mixture, swirl a spoonful on each serving and top with a cherry.
Chill until firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until soft; drain well.
Mix soup and sour cream; stir into squash and onion.
Add butter to stuffing mix; stir.
Put half of stuffing in bottom of 2-quart baking dish; add squash mixture. Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: old fashioned oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until brown and center is set.
Pie will puff up while baking, but will settle when cooled.

title: play dough
directions: *BLKLIN sliced or whole, small beets and let set 24 hours for pickled beets.

title: oven hash browns
directions: Peel and shred potatoes.
Transfer to a bowl and cover with water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove 1/4 cup of water from potatoes.
Place in a small saucepan with milk.
Cook just until hot.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine egg substitute, thyme, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Gradually add milk mixture, beating constantly.
Drain potatoes and press out excess liquid with paper towels.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients. Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in candy bars until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool on wire racks. Chilling in freezer is better.
You can use Butterfinger candy bars too.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and roll into balls.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Melt chocolates and wax on top of double boiler on low heat.
Makes about 75 balls.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together (except chocolate chips), until well blended.
Pour 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle (grease if necessary).
Drop around 6 or so chocolate chips onto each pancake. Cook until edges are dry.
Turn.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve with some fruit yogurt or syrup to taste.
Makes 12 to 13 pancakes.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker shell.
Chill until firm, about 5 hours or freeze.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Scoop out 1 cup hot mix and stir into egg yolks.
Add back into pudding and cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: Mix and let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Bring to slow boil and continue for 20 minutes.
Let stand with gauze cover, in sunshine if available, until thickened.
Seal and process.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with soda, spices and salt.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add the beaten egg, then the applesauce.
Add dry flour mixture, beating with each addition. Stir in raisins.
Pour into 8-inch square cake pan lined with wax paper on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or bake in muffin cups for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine squash, onion and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine with remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: etta's million dollar pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice, pineapple and mandarin oranges well.
Add nuts, blending well.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend together.
Pour mixture into crusts.
Cover with plastic liner from crusts' package (inverted).
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cindy's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, sugar and flour.
Add margarine, milk, eggs, and flavoring.
Bake on 400 degrees, for one hour.

title: grandma ada's poor man cake
directions: Cook water and raisins for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together plus the raisin mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9 -inch greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot pimiento dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in small baking dish at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: a real good pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife comes out of center clean.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Cut steak into strips and coat with flour mixture; brown on both sides with half of shortening.
Saute onion in remaining shortening until tender.
Place meat in baking dish.
Pour onion and shortening over meat.
Put potato halves over onions.
Pour tomato soup over potatoes.
Add garlic.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: linda's cherry cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients. Bake at 375° until done.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift the flour, powder, salt, sugar and cinnamon together. Cut in shortening until quite fine.
Combine egg, pumpkin and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until flour is well moistened. Fold in raisins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour water over bran and let cool.
Add buttermilk and molasses.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add the creamed mixture to the bran mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and raisins.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with one half of nuts.
Roll into a ball. Coat ball with remaining nuts.

title: percolator punch
directions: Percolate in a 30-cup coffee maker.*
This makes 30 (8 ounce) servings.
Leftovers may be served warm or cold.
Keeps well in a refrigerator.

title: strawberry-kiwi sugar-free pie
directions: Pour milk, pudding and Crystal Lite into large bowl; beat with mixer 2 minutes. Add Cool Whip and beat until blended. Pour into pie crust. Makes 2 pies.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice peppers long and thin.
Saute in oil with onions.
Cook until desired texture.
In separate pan, slice sirloin into thin strips and fry.
When cooked, add water, chicken broth and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch to desired thickness. Add ginger, peppers, onions and soy sauce. Continue simmering and stirring occasionally for 20 minutes. Serve over the cooked rice.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place half of lettuce in bottom of large, deep salad bowl. Layer celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Then add other half of lettuce.
Cover with mayonnaise and sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: baked macaroni, cheese and tuna
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth and return to heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in mustard, cheese and tuna.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Pour in a buttered casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: best ever roast
directions: Season roast; put into covered roasting pan with about 1-inch of water.
Bake, covered, at 325° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Check for doneness.
(Very tender and a great flavor.)

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, withholding 2 tablespoons of sugar and the cinnamon which is to be combined.
Pour bread mixture into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields about 10 slices.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Put pasta in large bowl.
Add chicken, celery, radishes, bell pepper and onions.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add to pasta and chicken and toss.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar in a large bowl. Beat 2 to 4 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan for 30 minutes before turning out.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together, roll by hand into small meatballs and fry in skillet.
When done, remove balls from skillet and remove excess fat.
In same skillet, pour in soup and water and heat through.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over noodles

title: microwave fish with cinnamon
directions: Melt butter in microwave dish with a cover.
Mix butter, lemon juice and cinnamon together.
Baste fillets with mixture in dish. Cook in microwave for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with long grain rice and cooked vegetables.

title: bible school strawberry country dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Add jello and milk. Beat with mixer until well blended and smooth.
Dip and enjoy!

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; let stand in cold water 3 to 4 hours.
Pack in jars.
Mix well the salt, sugar, dry mustard and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop drained artichokes.
Add garlic, mayonnaise and parsley. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with low salt Wheatables.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Yield:
6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans and 2/3 cup onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir. Sprinkle remaining 2/3 cup onions over bean mixture. Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: pink apple-lime punch
directions: Combine all in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill until serving time.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix
first
ingredients together and spread 1/4-inch thick on	a
greased
cookie sheet.
Beat egg white slightly; brush over
the dough.
Sprinkle over nuts.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut immediately size of popsicle sticks.

title: simple banana pudding
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool and add whipped cream.
Put layer of vanilla wafer crumbs in dish.
Spread small amount of cream mixture on crumbs.
Add bananas on top.
Spread rest of cream mixture over all.
Sprinkle a few wafer crumbs on cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Use as a basting sauce for pork, chicken or beef.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: pumpkin bread pudding(yields 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Slice bread into 1-inch cubes; set aside. Zest orange to measure 1 tablespoon. Pour evaporated milk into a microwave dish and microwave on High for 3 minutes or until hot. In another bowl, whisk pumpkin, 1/2 cup of sugar, eggs, pumpkin pie spice and orange zest until smooth. Gradually whisk hot milk into pumpkin mixture. Place half of bread cubes over bottom of a square pan, greased. Pour half of the pumpkin mixture over bread. Top with remaining bread cubes and remaining pumpkin mixture. Chop nuts and sprinkle evenly over bread. Sprinkle remaining 3 tablespoons sugar. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Serve with frozen yogurt or whipped topping.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 big loaves or several small ones.

title: mississippi mud
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour and salt; add eggs, nuts and cocoa mixture. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows (do not stick) and spread on icing.
Have icing ready when you take cake out of oven.

title: baked stuffed fillet of sole
directions: Place fish in buttered baking dish.
Put bread crumb mixture on each piece of fish; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add one of the following creamed soups: mushroom, shrimp or lobster Newburg sauce.
Mix with milk; pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste the fish with the sauce in the pan halfway through the baking time.

title: triple fudge brownies
directions: Prepare pudding according to box directions, but do not allow to set up. Immediately add cake mix and chips; blend together. Batter will be very thick. Spread into a large pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the middle springs back when touched. Allow to cool slightly, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt in a 2-quart pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes. more.
Add chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Stir until almost cool.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cool completely before cutting into pieces.

title: layered salad
directions: Spread lettuce evenly in bottom of 3-quart oblong casserole. Add layer of onions, green pepper, celery, peas and water chestnuts.
Pack these ingredients firmly into the pan, but do not mix.
Cover the entire top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Next, sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Follow with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese on top.
Do not mix. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight or longer.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand 2 hours.
Stir once in a while.
Rinse and drain.
Add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Add vinegar.
Mix, put pickles in freezer boxes and freeze.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix soup and milk until smooth.
Put a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Pour some of the soup mixture over all.
On top of this cover with the stuffing cubes.
Put rest of the soup mixture on top. Dot with butter. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: taco burger
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomatoes and green chilies, seasoning mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick.
Stir in chopped tomatoes.
Heat; divide and spoon on buns.
Top with lettuce and cheese.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Dredge with flour and the 1 1/2 teaspoons salt mixed and brown slowly in hot fat over moderate heat; add onions until soft.
Add 5 cups water and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.
Lift chicken out onto a plate to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to broth.
Simmer slowly for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, remove meat from bones and cut chicken into cubes. Return chicken to broth mixture.
Heat through quickly and serve at once.

title: pete's camp stew
directions: Chop potatoes, onions, green peppers and carrots into small cubes or strips.
Salt and pepper meat to taste.
Divide meat into 4 large patties and place in center of a 12 x 12-inch square of aluminum foil.
Add the potatoes, onions, green peppers and carrots around the patties.
Wrap the mixture, place in the hot coals of your campfire and cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Open and let cool for a few minutes.
You can make larger or smaller patties, but adjust the amount of vegetables accordingly.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except last three.
Divide dough into as many balls as you plan to make fruit.
The idea is to shape this dough into fruit shapes: strawberries, little peas in a pod, apples and bananas.
For each fruit you wish to make, you'll need to add enough food coloring to that portion of dough to make the color you desire.
You'll need red for strawberries, green for peas in the pod and yellow for apples and bananas.
Add the food coloring to make a good strong color because baking will cause the color to lighten.

title: cauliflower italiano
directions: Cook onion and garlic in salad dressing until tender.
Add cauliflower and 1/4 cup water.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Add green pepper, cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat.

title: teen's favorite manicotti
directions: Brown in skillet the ground meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste while meat is browning.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole with 1/2 of the Ragu sauce.
Add eggs, parsley and cheese to browned meat.

title: slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed together.
Pour over slaw.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add the onion, celery and green pepper.

title: carol's meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients together, except tomato sauce or barbecue sauce.
Shape into balls (golf ball size).
Brown in nonstick skillet.
Cover meat balls with either tomato sauce or barbecue sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: susan's dip
directions: Heat tomato soup and add gelatin. Stir to dissolve.
Beat in cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease mold with mayonnaise. Pour in mix and refrigerate.

title: cranberry glazed spareribs
directions: Brush both sides of ribs generously with Worcestershire sauce sauce and sprinkle with salt.
Place ribs on a rack in a large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until they form a lump in middle of pan.
Thoroughly beat by hand the eggs (one at a time) into flour mixture.
Spread in jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inches).
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Note:
Will not use all of brownies.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Combine all ingredients together.
Divide dough in half.
Mix red food coloring in 1/2 dough.
Roll dough in a strip (each color).
Place side by side and twist into cane effect.
Before baking, sprinkle over canes 1/2 cup crushed peppermint and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as stated on package with no salt.
Cook Minute rice.
Saute onion.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: speedy oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients until smooth; then add next 3 ingredients. Mix well. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain.
Stir in and saute small amount of onion and green pepper.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa.

title: so good apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cooled margarine and eggs.
Add apples, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Bake in unbaked crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Mix chicken, water chestnuts, celery and grapes together.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken mixture and stir. Chill several hours.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's raisin stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until soft, but not brown. Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add raisins and cook until plump.
Mix all together.
Stuff bird or bake in buttered baking dish for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Fry on nonstick pan.

title: pizza salad
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Put in dish and add anything you would put on a pizza such as pepperoni slices, mushrooms, olives, onions, peppers, cheese, Italian seasoning, oregano, etc.
Add oil and mix together.
Place in fridge until ready to eat.

title: meringue stabilizer
directions: Combine water, sugar
and
cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring
constantly,
until
transparent
and thickened. Cool. Beat egg
whites
and salt until foamy. Continue beating while pouring cooked
mixture
into whites.
Beat 3 minutes or until stiff peaks form.

title: dad's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo and both sugars together; add eggs and mix.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Add flour, soda and vanilla; mix well. Roll into small loaves; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Slice thin and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and place a layer of noodles on bottom of dish.
Place layer of boned and skinned chicken.
Next place layer of soups and mushrooms, mixed together, then add a layer of grated cheese.
Continue until 3 layers are completed.
Top with noodles and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: corn, tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Chop tomato and cucumber into cubes.
Mix all ingredients together and add mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: In a saucepan, boil together the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk, for 3 minutes (this should be a fast boil to cook the sugar).
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in saucepan.
Boil about 1 minute.
Then add vanilla, peanut butter and Special K and stir.
Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: french chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer on high speed.
Add chocolate (melt chocolate and cool) to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and 1 whole egg.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Add second egg. Beat 5 minutes again.
Turn into an 8-inch baked pie shell. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Wrap; store at least 1 day.

title: lemon lush
directions: For Crust:
Mix flour and butter; add pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water; drain and mash (instant potatoes also work).
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Spread in buttered pan.
Can also be topped with Cheddar cheese if desired.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to use, drizzle melted butter over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Gravy also goes well on these.

title: swedish christmas porridge
directions: Scald rice with boiling water.
Melt half of butter.
Add rice and water; boil 10 to 15 minutes or until water disappears.
Add milk and cook slowly 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Season and add remainder of butter.
Pour into deep dish and serve with cold milk, cinnamon and sugar.

title: onion shortcake casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
In skillet melt butter and saute onions 5-6 minutes or till soft. Remove from heat and stir in half of the cheddar cheese, sour cream, dill and salt until combined.
In bowl, lightly beat egg. Stir in muffin mix, cream corn, milk and tabasco.
Spread into prepared casserole dish.
Top with cheese and onion mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheddar.
Bake 35-40 minutes until top is golden.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, omitting salt in cooking water; drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli cuts in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese. Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli in a baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over soup in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 325°
about 45 minutes or until done.
Top with meringue.
Make by beating egg whites and adding 1/2 cup
sugar to vanilla until fluffy.
Spread on pie.
Bake until brown.
Let cool 30 to 40 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: spinach "brownies"
directions: Drain spinach in colander and squeeze out moisture.
Combine cheese, spinach and onion in a large bowl, mixing well.
Stir salt, baking powder and nutmeg into flour, then mix with spinach. Mix together beaten eggs, melted butter and milk.
Stir into other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with foil.
Spray with Pam and pour in spinach mixture.
Bake about 35 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool completely. Remove from foil lining and cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes about 40 small squares.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fleischkuechle
directions: Mix together to form a soft dough.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir together with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together jello, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Stir until it turns all orange, then add pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Mix well together and chill for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a cookie sheet with oil substitute. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups together; pour 1/2 of mixture into an aluminum foil-lined 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over soup mixture. Drizzle butter over rice.
Top with chicken pieces and pour remainder of soup on top.
Cover pan with foil and bake 4 hours in oven at 275°.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions. Put tomatoes in pie shell. Sprinkle with basil and onions. Mix mayonnaise and cheese. Spread on top of tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts and tomatoes are hot. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: roman holiday
directions: Brown beef until all red is gone; drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Stir before serving.
Good with corn bread on a cold day.

title: just floating
directions: Thoroughly mix brandy, water, wine and lime juice in fountain. Add sugar; mix to dissolve.
Garnish with quartered lemons, nutmeg and toasted biscuits.
Place attendant with dipper in rowboat and float in fountain.
Dip and serve.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook the first six ingredients twenty minutes.
Strain, add salt and soda and blend, and strain into tureen.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Combine remaining ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 additional minutes.
Transfer to chafing dish and keep warm.

title: creme de menthe sophisticated treat
directions: Pour a little green lemon sherbet for a cool dessert with a sophisticated atmosphere.
Serve in a clear glass champagne glass or dish.
Serve with your favorite dessert cookie.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine spinach and cream cheese.
Stir until melted and blended.
Alternate layers of spinach, soup and onion rings in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour on top.
Sprinkle with pecans before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Reserve small amount of powdered sugar to sprinkle on top of cake when done.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain, rinse in cold water and drain again.
Place in large bowl, mixing all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
Keeps at least a week in refrigerator.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and oil.
Beat well.
Cook in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix sugar and lemon juice well.
Pour 1/2 mixture over cake as soon as it comes from oven. After cake is removed from pan, add remaining icing.

title: cheeseburger fried pie
directions: Brown ground meat until no longer pink. Drain ground meat and return meat to skillet. Add both cans of soup and seasoning and mix well. Pour meat mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place frozen fries in a single layer on top of meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese bubbles over the top.

title: poppy seed dressing(makes 1 quart)
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine the first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add the oil and beat until thick, then beat 5 minutes more.
Add the poppy seed and blend well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine shortening, 1 1/2 c. sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Gradually add to first mixture, blending well.
Roll dough into walnut-sized balls.
Combine cinnamon and 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Roll balls in cinnamon mixture. Place on greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk, let stand until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Alternate layers of crackers and pudding mixture ending with cracker layer on top.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and spices.
Coat berries with sugar mixture.
Place berry mixture in a shallow 8 1/2 inch round casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Meantime invert frozen pie crust on waxed paper.
Let thaw until completely flat.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk, then add other ingredients.
Pour in two graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Put together ingredients. Add milk or water or a little of each.
Make as thick as you like.

title: crispy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to butter and sugars (creamed together quite well), vanilla and eggs.
Beat into sugar and butter well.
Gradually add to all the ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto oiled cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: italian connection gourmet's braciolone(serves 3 to 5)
directions: Mix together the ground meat, Romano cheese, raw eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Boil chicken breasts without skin until done.
Cut up into bite-sized pieces.
Mix with sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Pour into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or margarine, stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended; continue cooking 2 minutes.
Stirring constantly.
Gradually stir milk and cook until sauce is thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat; set aside stirring occasionally to prevent a skim from forming on sauce.

title: hot john
directions: Cook all this until well done and pack into jars and seal. Make sure that your jars are hot.

title: easy chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in large pan. Simmer until done, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: plain layer cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder and salt. Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla. Bake in 2 layer pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Melt butter; add and slightly brown the celery and onion.
Add soup, broth, Tabasco, chicken and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Place in buttered casserole; top with cashew nuts and noodles. Place in a 350° oven until heated through.
Serves 10.

title: creamy vanilla frosting
directions: Beat powdered sugar, butter and vanilla until blended.
Add milk, beating well. Add additional milk, 1/4 tsp. at a time until desired consistency.

title: farris' dark fruit cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix eggs, sugars and oil in large bowl.
Sift together dry ingredients in small bowl.
To oil, sugar and egg mixture, add flour mixture alternately with 1 (6-ounce) can of pineapple juice.
Pour batter over floured fruit and nut mix, taking care to mix well.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out onto cake rack.
When cake is cold, wrap in foil and store in covered container.
Yields 5 1/2-pound cake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 8 x 12 inch pan.
In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine shredded carrots, coconut, walnuts, pineapple and raisins.
Using a large wooden spoon or a very heavy whisk, add carrot mixture to batter and fold in well.
Pour into prepared 8 x 12 inch pan, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check with toothpick. Allow to cool for at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: 30 minute cake frosting
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and milk to a boil, then add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on cake while cake is still warm.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Then in pot with 6 to 8 cups of water, bring to a boil, simmer 2 minutes, cover and let soak for 1 hour.
Then return beans to a boil, add ham bone and simmer beans 1 hour until tender.
Remove bone and remove ham from bone.
Add ham and other ingredients to beans, cover and simmer until other vegetables are tender.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and garlic to taste.
Mix enough Miracle Whip to make the salad creamy.
Chill overnight for the best results.

title: spaghetti mix
directions: Add mix to one pound of hamburger while browning.

title: potato casserole
directions: Prepare 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Pour potatoes, then chopped onion in pan; mix them up a little.
Melt oleo and pour half over potatoes and onion in the pan.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix all together, except crackers.
Coat crackers with mixture, tossing until well coated, about 5 or 6 minutes.

title: moravian mints(nazareth)
directions: Put sugar and water in top of double boiler; after sugar is dissolved, add flavoring.
When mixture hardens slightly on the top, it is ready to drop on wax paper.

title: raspberry buttermilk sipper
directions: In a food processor or blender, process raspberries until smooth. If you don't like the seeds, strain the puree. Put the puree back into the blender and add the rest of the ingredients. Process until smooth. Cover and chill.

title: pralines
directions: Break crackers into sections and lay into a shallow pan (cookie sheet or jelly roll pan).
Melt butter and add sugar. Boil for 3 minutes on medium heat.
Add nuts and vanilla; spread over crackers.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Take out of pan immediately and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly; drain and cool.
Mix enchilada sauce and tomato sauce and 3 cups water in big saucepan. Blend thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Cut down heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Fry shells and drain on paper towels.
Roll or stack enchilada.
Bake about 15 minutes and serve.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep casserole dish or baking pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well. Pour this batter over melted margarine and add peaches.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
The fruit will sink and the batter will rise to the top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix butter, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour mix, then pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ashley's sandwich stacker
directions: Take 2 pieces of bread.
Put cheese, then lunch meat and repeat.
Add mayonnaise or mustard.

title: mexican roll-ups #1
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese, chilies, olives, onions and Tabasco sauce together; spread on tortillas.
Roll up the tortillas jelly-roll style.
Refrigerate briefly or overnight in a plastic bag.
Slice in 1-inch pieces before serving.
Serve with medium picante sauce/salsa for dipping.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix Philly cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together at medium speed until blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour batter into ready to use graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results, refrigerate 3 hours.
Garnish as desired.
I like blueberry pie filling on top.

title: 24-hour bean salad
directions: Pour cooled liquid over beans.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Stir about 3 times during refrigeration.
This salad will keep up to three weeks.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers and cover with 1 pint Hellmann's mayonnaise. Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Top with bacon and cheese.

title: mini-mounds
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into extra large mixing bowl.
Pour in sugar and mix well.
Add coconut and pecans and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and put in freezer for 45 minutes.
Remove and cut into bite sized pieces.
Melt chocolate in double boiler with paraffin and dip pieces into chocolate.
Keep chocolate in double boiler while dipping.

title: herbed eggs
directions: Remove and mash yolks with yogurt, mayonnaise and mustard. Season with herbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Pile mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with dill sprigs.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll biscuits in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Drop in a greased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan. Melt butter or margarine, mix with brown sugar and pour over the biscuits.
Be sure to place the pan on a cookie sheet because it will leak.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Stir constantly until completely melted.
Add other ingredients.
Pour onto waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Form and let cool completely.
Cut and serve. Yields approximately 2 pounds.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat until foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine dry ingredients, walnuts and currants.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture until well blended. Bake at 350° in loaf pan.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel banana; break into chunks with fingers.
Put chunks in medium bowl; mash with a fork until there are no lumps.
Pour in milk and vanilla; beat with eggbeater until smooth and foamy.
Pour into glasses and serve.

title: very easy french onion soup
directions: Microwave butter and onions on High for 15 minutes.
Stir. Stir in instant bouillon, beef bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Divide into bowls.
Top with croutons and Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted.

title: self-frosted date cake
directions: Put dates in a bowl and cover with boiling water.
Add soda; cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour with salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in cooled date mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Combine sugar, nuts and chocolate chips and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki salmon
directions: Place salmon in flat dish or resealable plastic bag. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl

and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour marinade over fish and marinate for 15 minutes. Drain salmon and place in baking dish. Grill, broil or microwave. Halfway through cooking time, baste with marinade. Grill/broil 10 minutes per inch of thickness; do not turn. Microwave, covered with waxed paper, at 70% power for 3 minutes per inch of thickness.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: First, mix and bake cake as directed on bake.
Second, while cake is still warm, poke holes in cake and pour milk over top and caramel syrup.
Third, cool cake.
Put Cool Whip on top of cake and crumbled Butterfinger on top of Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Layer meat, sliced onion, squash and Cheez Whiz.
Make 2 layers.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over layers. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Beat the eggs well.
Add oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix all ingredients.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add onion and Mrs. Dash blend.
You may use more or less of onion and Mrs.
Dash according to your taste.
Chop Velveeta cheese and blend in with beef/sausage.
Spread on party rye bread and place slices on cookie sheet or tray that will fit in microwave.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: *mititei("hamburg sausage")
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Set in refrigerator for a few hours.
Roll 1/3 cup into sausage shape.
Cook over a hot fire on an outside grill or broil in oven.
Makes 20 pieces.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt on plate (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Cook on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Cook for 3 1/2 minutes on High. Add butter and vanilla; stir.
Cook 2 more minutes on High.
Add baking soda; stir well.
Pour onto cookie sheet to cool 1 hour. Break apart when set.

title: felecia's beans
directions: Chop bacon.
Brown in skillet. Add hamburger and brown.
Drain fat.
Add onions, saute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth; reserve 3 cups of broth. Reserve remaining broth for another use, if desired.
Let chicken cool; cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Skim fat from broth.

title: yellow charlotte russe
directions: Put gelatin into the milk to soften in top of double boiler while you beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Heat milk to dissolve gelatin and add egg and sugar mixture.
Cook mix in the double boiler until it coats spoon.
Cool.
When cool, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites; fold in whipped cream and flavoring. Pour into mold and allow to get firm before serving.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine and let stand 20 minutes. Mix well. Add eggs, vanilla, white sugar and brown sugar. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to mixture. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add evaporated milk, condensed sweetened milk and vanilla.
Then heat well over double boiler; add peaches and pour into gallon freezer.
Finish filling with milk and freeze.
When frozen, pour water from ice cream freezer and pack with ice.
Let set to mellow for better flavor.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine beef bones, water or stock, salt, pepper and bay leaf in a large kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Remove bones and skim fat if necessary.
Cut off, chop and reserve meat.
Add barley.
Continue cooking about 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add any leftover vegetables available.
Heat through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fried clam fritters
directions: Make batter; add clams.
Dip clams in batter and add to deep fat fryer at 375° to 400°.

title: super rice
directions: Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Do not overcook.

title: glazed london broil
directions: Mix seasonings well.
Pour over either London broil or flank steak.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour, turning meat from side to side.
(Can also marinate all day in the refrigerator.)

title: beef stroganoff-light
directions: Partially freeze meat.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-sized strips.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt (optional).
Coat meat with flour mixture.
In nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray, brown meat on both sides.
Add the mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Remove the meat/mushroom/onion mixture from the skillet.
Add beef broth to pan drippings.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato paste and salt to season.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir over medium high heat until bubbly.
Cook up to 2 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Combine sour cream and remaining flour.
Return meat/mushroom mixture and wine; heat but do not boil.

title: tropical fruit 'n nut bars
directions: Drain pineapple.
Sprinkle gelatin over juice.	Let stand one minute.
Stir over low heat until dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in honey, pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Turn into 9x9-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into bars. 16 servings.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Brown chuck roast.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in 250° oven for about 6 hours.
Mash meat with potato masher.
Serve on buns.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop and set aside.
Pour cooking oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour to mixture and vanilla.
Gently fold in chopped apples.
Pour into 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
When cool, drizzle on sugar glaze.

title: chicken soup and dumplings
directions: Cover all with water.
Cook until chicken breast and legs are tender.
Remove to frying pan with 1/4 pound butter or oleo melted.
Fry slowly until chicken is golden brown.

After removing chicken to pan, place 1 package frozen stewing vegetables or 6 medium potatoes (peeled), 3 slices onion, 1/2 package frozen cauliflower or 1/2 head fresh cauliflower, 1 package frozen mixed vegetables or peas and carrots.
Cook until potatoes have begun to boil.
Add dumplings by teaspoon until all in.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, then cover tight for 12 more minutes; serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order listed.
Top with mayonnaise and bacon bits.
Chill overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in shallow greased 2-quart casserole; add water. Combine sugars, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and flour.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Spoon crumbled mixture evenly over apples. Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips and mix well.
Add flour and nuts.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with the bottom of a greased glass dipped in sugar.
Put a cherry half or quarter on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour gradually to make a soft dough.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut out. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant supreme
directions: Saute meat with seasonings and pine nuts.
Add onions and continue sauteing until soft.
Set aside.
Slice eggplants approximately 1-inch thick rounds.
Brown eggplant in butter until slightly brown and soft.
Place the rounds in a baking dish (1 layer).
Place meat mixture onto each slice, then place a layer of eggplant on top.
Pour tomato sauce over eggplants and barely cover with water.
Sprinkle with additional salt.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove gently with a pancake turner and place over a serving of rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: thanksgiving pickles
directions: Pack whole cucumbers in 1/2 gallon jar. Mix vinegar, salt, spices and alum together.
Pour over cucumbers. Finish filling jar with cold water.
Put Saran Wrap on jar; seal tight and set aside. In fall when you want to eat, take out of jar and dry off.
Slice pickles about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Pour about 1 1/2 pounds sugar over them; seal and shake jar to dissolve sugar.
Leave in refrigerator as you use them.
The longer they set, the crispier they get.

title: chow han (japan)
directions: Saute garlic in oil until brown (set aside).
Saute onion and green pepper until transparent (set aside).
Cook eggs in pancake shape, cut into strips (set aside).
Brown beef lightly; add ham, shrimp and cook over medium heat.
Add rice, one cup at a time, stirring to separate.
Add eggs to rice mixture.
Toss lightly, season with soy sauce.
(Optional:
Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts.)
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked pork chops with lima beans(mama's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fast-fry chops, browning lightly on each side.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into large casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay chops on top and bake at 375° for about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not let beans cook dry.
Turn chops after 1/2 hour (or more, if necessary).
Serve with tossed green salad and hot biscuits!

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Layer broccoli in a greased 12 x 8 inch baking pan.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic and spread over the chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix the bread crumbs and melted butter with fork until moist, and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot layered mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients (in order listed) in baking dish. Bake in moderate oven until thoroughly heated. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peasant vegetable soup
directions: Pick over beans and rinse.
Soak overnight in water.
Saute onions, leeks, celery and carrots in oil and cook covered over low heat until tender, about 25 minutes.
Stir in thyme, bay leaf and stock.
Add parsnips, ham and soaked beans and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer partially covered until beans are tender, about 40 minutes.
Add cabbage and garlic and simmer for another 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pork and peppers
directions: Cut roast into 2-inch cubes.
Chop garlic very small or crush it.
Pour enough oil to cover bottom of pan.
Heat and brown meat and garlic.
Drain oil off.
Pour soy sauce, water and sugar over meat.
Simmer until tender.
Quarter onions and slice bell peppers and jalapeno peppers.
Cook slowly until onions and peppers are tender.
If you like it hot, cut 2 or 3 of the jalapenos.
Serve over rice.

title: meatballs
directions: Put crackers in a bowl with milk and let them absorb the milk. When soggy, break into small pieces and add the spices and egg. Mix well, then add the meats.
Mix together until well blended. Using a 1 1/2 ounce scoop, make into meatballs, placing on a large pizza pan with a little salad oil coating pan to keep meat from burning.
Cook for 20 minutes or until done in a 300° preheated oven.
Makes a large amount.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients except wine and shrimp. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until spices are cooked.
Add wine and simmer 10 minutes.
Put approximately 15 shrimp in aluminum foil pouches and pour sauce mixture over shrimp.
Cook in oven at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hershey's syrup brownies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat mixture. Stir in Hershey's syrup, flour, salt and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: world's best granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine oats, almonds, flour, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Whisk together oil, maple syrup and vanilla. Combine with dry ingredients.
Spread out on a large pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn oven off and leave in oven for several more hours.
The granola will be dry and crunchy.

title: fettuccine with alfredo sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain. Melt butter over medium heat. Add whipping cream. Stir in cheese. Add parsley. Toss sauce with hot pasta.

title: honey buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent rolls and divide into scored

title: red pepper jam
directions: Remove seeds and mid-ribs from peppers.
Run through food chopper; measure.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours. Add sugar and vinegar; cook until thick.
Pour into hot jars. Seal at once.

title: tequila slush
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in soda and tequila.
Pour mixture into freezer container; freeze until firm. Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving; stir until slushy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1 stick of melted butter and press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks butter and powdered sugar for 13 minutes at high speed and put on top of cracker crumbs.
Put a layer of sliced bananas, sliced lengthwise.
Next a layer of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in drained, whole kernel corn. Drop from spoon into skillet in hot oil.
Fry on both sides like a pancake.
Cook 2 to 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper towel.

title: english muffins
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Mix it with the milk, salt, sugar and shortening in a bowl and let cool to lukewarm.
Stir the yeast into 1/4 cup warm water and let stand for 5 minutes to dissolve.
Add the dissolved yeast and 2 cups of flour to the mixture and beat very fast.
Mix well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Stir.
Add the remaining flour and beat well.
Cover and let dough double in bulk once again. Turn out onto a lightly floured board and pat the dough until it is 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 3 inch rounds.
Cover and let rise until almost double.
Cook on well-greased griddle or skillet until done.
Cook on each side.
Cool and then split in half.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine bacon
and cream cheese and fill mushroom caps. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: hawaiian supreme cake
directions: Sift cake mix and pudding together.
Add eggs, one at a time, then oil, then 7-Up.
Mix all together and pour in three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin swirl
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan lined with waxed paper which is well-greased.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix and spread on cake.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Fry steak in oil until brown; do not flour.
Add onion soup mix and water; mix well.
Simmer about 30 minutes until done.
Add strips of green pepper; cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water; add to mixture.
Stir until thick.

title: pecan caramel creme squares
directions: Place caramels, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler. Cook, stirring occasionally until mixture is melted and smooth (approximately 25 minutes).
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Press remainder into pan or dish. Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.

title: bourbon-spiked apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients except bourbon in a large pot. Bring to the boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium. Simmer until reduced to about 12 cups, 30 minutes or so. Remove from heat. With slotted spoon, remove cloves and cinnamon sticks. Mix bourbon into cider. Serve warm or cold.

title: spanish potato omelet
directions: Fry bacon in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon and drain, reserving 4 tablespoons bacon fat in skillet.
Cook and stir potato and onion in skillet until potato is golden brown and tender, about 10 minutes.

title: kudzuki(greek sauce)
directions: Blend together in a blender until smooth.
In Greece they use yogurt but Americans prefer sour cream, so experiment using yogurt.
Let mixture set for at least an hour, it "gathers strength" with time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in pan, 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch. Mix other ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice and broccoli according to directions on package.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Bake until top is brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put into a bowl and mix with a fork.
Then roll into balls and put on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Then bake until brown in 250° oven.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain the clams and save the juice.
In a heavy saucepot, melt butter and slowly stir in flour to make a white sauce.
Using a wire whip, slowly stir in clam sauce and water to the white sauce. Bring to a
boil, stirring constantly to keep liquid smooth.
Add clams, potatoes and onions; simmer until tender.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Season with salt and white pepper. Serve with oyster soup crackers.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind the vegetables.
Mix with the vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Seal hot.
Makes approximately 10 pints.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Cook turkey and onions in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add vinegar, chili powder, oregano, cumin and cayenne pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in beans and water.
Put 2 tablespoons salsa in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Place 1/2 tortilla strips on top of salsa.
Top with 1/2 of turkey mixture and half of remaining salsa.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place breasts, skin side up, in an oblong baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, including mushroom liquid.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream tea biscuits
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls in miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can bake early until muffins are set but not browned; then pop back in oven to reheat.
Serve piping hot.
No need to serve with butter.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Saute meat and onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add other ingredients to meat and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Simmer 1 hour on low.
Cook in a heavy pan and stir often as it tends to stick.

title: hot tuna biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pat each biscuit into a thin 4-inch oval.
Arrange half of biscuits on a greased cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, mix tuna, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spoon on biscuits on cookie sheet.
Top with remaining biscuits.
With fingers, press edges together.
Bake sandwiches 10 to 15 minutes until browned. Makes 10 sandwiches.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, egg, bread crumbs and salt.
Shape into small 1/2-inch meatballs. Arrange in shallow baking pan. Broil 4-inches from heat until browned.
Turn once.
Pour off fat.

title: clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and saute garlic and parsley flakes.
Add tomatoes. Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add clams and simmer 5 to 7 minutes more.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: bavarian casserole(kielbasa)
directions: Mix all.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Cut beans in 1 1/2-inch pieces; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Toss with onion, pimento and garbanzo beans.
Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: health bread
directions: Pour warm-to-hot water into large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle dry yeast into water.
Add sugar, salt.
Sift and measure 3 c. unbleached flour, stir into above mixture.
Let rest 20 minutes.

title: baked snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter.
Add vegetables. Saute 10 minutes.
Mix in bread crumbs, spices, juice of lemon and wine vinegar.
Stir over low heat 3 minutes.
Spoon on snapper fillets. Bake 30 minutes.

title: apple cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food chopper using medium blade.
Dice apples and combine with cranberry mixture.
Add nut meats, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meat and remove excess fat.
Put everything in large stockpot.
Cover and cook on medium to low heat.
Stir contents 3 times in first 15 minutes.
Cook 35 minutes or until rice is done.

title: herbed italian chicken
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add chicken, pepperoni and garlic; stir-fry about 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Remove chicken mixture from skillet; keep warm.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, sour cream and then dry ingredients.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Place on lightly floured board; roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Remove to cooling racks.
Can be covered with a powdered sugar and water frosting and then decorated.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil, garlic powder, dill weed and Ranch dressing mix in a jar.
Shake well to mix thoroughly.
Pour over oyster crackers in a container with a lid.
Shake well.
Let sit for at least 2 hours, shaking and stirring every half hour.
These can be made days ahead and store in an airtight container.

title: cossack mold
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in water, stir over low heat until dissolved.
Cool.
Combine mayonnaise and horseradish and gradually stir in gelatin.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold; chill until almost firm.
Drain beets (add water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups).
Dissolve lemon gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add beet juice and vinegar; chill until thickened.
Stir in beets and cabbage.
Put in mold over first layer.
Chill until firm; unmold. Garnish as desired.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in flour. Add milk.
Add chicken broth and cheese.
Add vegetables and dash of celery seed. Add pepper.
Blend all ingredients and heat through over low heat.

title: pork chops and hominy
directions: Season pork chops and brown in oil in large skillet. Add water to meat and drippings to coat bottom of skillet.
Add Worcestershire sauce and hominy.
Pour more water over top for simmering and cooking down.
Add water periodically as it cooks. Salt and pepper. Cover.
Cooking time is approximately 30 minutes.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bananas.
Stir well.
Add bananas and stir gently.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze overnight.
Allow to thaw about 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: chocolate tarts
directions: Make dough and roll out as for apple turnovers.
Mix cocoa and sugar.
Put in desired amount, 1/4 to 1/2-inch turnover shells. Bake instead of frying.
Butter tops before frying.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or fry as desired.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. Mix together and let jell.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large boiler and let come to a boil.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Have lids hot. Pack in cans and seal.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Take 1 cup berries, sugar and 1 cup water, put in saucepan and simmer until berries are mushy.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch (dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into berries).
Cook until thickened.
Add 3 cups blueberries.
Mix well.
Put in baked pie shell.
Serve with whip topping.

title: faye's caramel popcorn
directions: Stir jelly in a small saucepan over medium low heat until melted and smooth.
Stir in peppers and vinegar; pour into 3 hot clean (6 ounce) jars dividing peppers evenly among them.
Stir to distribute peppers evenly.
Cover loosely and refrigerate.
When cold, tighten lids.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef in hot fat in a skillet. Mix tomato sauce, mixed vegetables, salt and pepper in casserole dish. Add browned onions and beef. Cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Place butter in saute pan.
Melt and add carrots, mushrooms, peppers, scallions and broccoli.
Saute about 3 to 5 minutes.
Once cooked, add heavy cream.
Bring mixture to a low boil.
Add fettuccine and stir.
Add garlic and some of the Parmesan cheese. Stir until Parmesan cheese disappears and then add more cheese. Sauce should be thick, then add seasonings.
Serve immediately. Serves 2 to 4.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix dry jello into
the whipped topping; add the cottage cheese and mix well.
Add the drained pineapple and nuts.
Chill before serving, at least a couple of hours.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
(Freezes well.)

title: coconut-pecan icing
directions: Heat over medium heat the milk, margarine and sugar.
Heat for 12 minutes until thick.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Spread on a 3 layered German chocolate cake.
Frost tops only.
Double recipe to frost sides and tops.

title: oat bran muffins(helps body get rid of choc)
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: arabian chicken and shrimp salad
directions: Mix chicken, rice, shrimp and cucumber.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, French dressing and chili sauce.
Add chicken mix to dressing mixture.
Stir gently.
Serve on lettuce with tomato wedges and olives.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Stir-fry green curry paste for 1 minute. Add chicken and nampla. Stir-fry until chicken is done. Add coconut milk and bring to a boil. Add sweet peas and green chillies.
Stir a few times.
Remove from heat.

title: mexican steak
directions: Brown steak good in Crisco or lard.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder while browning meat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery, cut up.
Saute real good.
Add tomatoes, cumin powder and water after meat is browned.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and take off bones.
Cook dumplings in broth until done.
Add more water as needed.
Add chicken, soup and milk.
Simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bran rolls
directions: Put Crisco, bran, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add boiling water, stirring until shortening is melted.
Let mixture stand until lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water and add to mixture.
Add half flour and beat until batter is smooth.
Add remaining flour and beat well.
Cover bowl closely and place in refrigerator overnight or until ready to use.
Roll on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put small amount of soft butter on top and fold over to make Parkerhouse rolls.
Place close together on a baking sheet. Let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: company burgers
directions: Brown onions, meat and pepper.
Add other ingredients except soup.
Cook awhile; add soup.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Toast hamburger buns in oven, then spoon on filling.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Option:
Use strawberry Jell-O and 1 cup strawberries.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the mashed potatoes, granulated sugar, 1/2 cup of the butter, the eggs, vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix well and place in an 8-inch square greased baking dish.
Mix together the remaining 2 1/2 tablespoons butter, the brown sugar, flour and nuts and distribute evenly over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Combine cooked noodles with cottage cheese, eggs, sugar, milk and salt.
Pour into well-greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour, or until knife comes out clean.
Cool and refrigerate in pan 8 hours or overnight.
Cut into 3-inch squares without removing from pan.
Reheat at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Brown cube steak and green peppers in the oil.
Stir in the water, brown gravy mix and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients into casserole dish.
(Macaroni should be cooked first.)
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Feeds 4 to 6.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Bake white cake mix as directed on box, adding 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake in 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Cool cake.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: joy's barbecue shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in baking pan.
Melt butter and pour over shrimp. Sprinkle heavily with garlic powder 3 times across the pan.
Add lemon pepper seasoning, Italian seasoning and white pepper one time across pan with each.
Sprinkle with shrimp boil.
Add cracked pepper heavily.
Add thyme lightly.
Bake at 350°, turning every few minutes, until the shrimp are done.
Serve with lots of napkins!

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Add 2 beaten eggs, melted butter, milk and can of corn.
Blend well.
Pour in ungreased casserole baking dish (350° for 45 minutes).

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk, cheese and 1/4 teaspoon garlic in a mixer bowl.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine margarine and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder in bowl.
Brush over warm biscuits.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: full meal broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in	saucepan.
Saute
onions
until tender. Add 4 tablespoons cornstarch and	mix well.
Add 1 quart milk. Cook slowly, stirring
constantly.
Add	cheese;
stir
until melted. Add broccoli, ham and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with onion/garlic croutons or garlic bread.

title: lemon curd(served as a spread or tarts.)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until somewhat thickened.
Do not let it boil.
It thickens as it cools. Pour into glass jars once it is cooled.

title: shirley's spinach cheese pie
directions: Prick pie crust with fork and bake in a preheated 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Layer 1/2 spinach and 1/2 Swiss or Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.

title: purple cow(beverage)
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender.

title: potato skin snack
directions: Scrub potatoes and coat with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
(Save and use pulp for other uses.)
Cut shells into 5 (1/2-inch wide) strips.
Place strips, skin side down, on a baking sheet.
Brush with dressing; sprinkle with seasoning blend.
Broil 6 inches from heat 5 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm.

title: oven steak
directions: Place steak and salt/pepper on one side in a long pan.
Pour dressing over steak.
Place in oven at 350° and cook for 45 minutes.
Turn steak and cook another 15 minutes.
The juice makes great gravy for mashed potatoes.

title: imperial crab
directions: Remove crusts. Cube bread very small and add to sauce, eggs, mustard and Tabasco.
Add 1 pound backfin crabmeat; mix well. Put in shells and coat with mayonnaise. Garnish with pimento and olives. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; pour on butter.
Do not stir.
Pour in fruit.
Do not stir. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving time and then toss with your favorite vinaigrette dressing.

title: mushroom pate
directions: Saute 1 pound mushrooms in butter until all liquid is absorbed.
Cool.
Position knife blade in food processor.
Add mushrooms, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Process until smooth, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Spoon mixture into a greased loaf pan.
Chill.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Roll dough in small balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place far apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with tortillas or corn chips. Mix all of the other ingredients (except onion rings), adding the chicken last. Pour over tortillas or corn chips. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly. Top with Durkee onion rings just before taking out of the oven, if desired.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into pieces and boil for 10 minutes or until soft.
Drain potatoes and add sour cream, cream cheese, milk and margarine.
Use mixer and blend until smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger and potato thing
