directions: Combine all ingredients, adding 1/2 of onion rings last.
Mix well.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings over top last 5 minutes.
Remove; let sit 5 minutes before serving.
This is good to make ahead and refrigerate until ready to use.
Baking time will be longer if refrigerated.

title: banana split tarte
directions: First Layer:
Graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; mix and press firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: company spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add garlic and celery; brown, stirring constantly.
Mix rice, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, bay leaf and cayenne with hot water.
Add to garlic and celery in skillet; stir well and cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Brown beef and green pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chili powder, sugar and beef bouillon.
Combine rice and meat mixtures in 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add water or tomato juice, if necessary.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: asparagus appetizers
directions: Blanch asparagus and cool.
Spread softened cream cheese on ham slices.
Wrap ham slices around asparagus spears.
Good appetizer during asparagus season.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables.
Add mayonnaise and cheese.
Put in casserole. Top with crackers mixed with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix eggs, 1 2/3 cups sugar, oil and pumpkin together until fluffy.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, salt and soda; mix together until smooth.
Pour into smaller greased and floured cookie sheet pans so cake will come out about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until done (test with toothpick in center) at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Scrape sides of bowl frequently.
Add egg. Beat until blended.
Combine flours, salt and baking soda.
Bake into creamed mixture at low speed of electric mixer or by hand with a large spoon until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into a mound on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes (cookies will appear moist).
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling racks.

title: tater tot casserole(very easy)
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch casserole, combine ground beef, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Pat down to cover bottom of dish. Spread soups on top of beef mixture.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into serving size balls. Pour an additional cup of tomato juice over all.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: evelyn's pork roast
directions: Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° with marinade 3 hours or more!
Thicken with flour or cornstarch for gravy.
Slice; add little gravy on slices.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Brush pie crust with egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes; set aside.
Spoon pie filling into pie crust.
In small bowl combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm sprinkled with confectioners sugar as desired.
Garnish with apple slices.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add 2 eggs and beat.
Add flour and beat, then add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla.
The more you beat, the lighter your cake will be.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: italian beef (venison)
directions: Cook roast in oven.
Slice roast when done.
Combine the remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Combine roast and boiled mixture together in crock-pot.
Cook at low heat all day.
Serve on buns.

title: clams casino
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Place cherrystones on a baking pan. Place a small amount of the chopped onion and pepper combination on each clam. Add a small pad of garlic butter to each clam. Sprinkle each clam with bread crumbs. Place a bacon square on top of each clam. Bake for about 10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix milk with well beaten egg.
Mix with dry ingredients; beat thoroughly.
Mix in corn and melted butter.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot oil.
Cook until well browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Boil together the cauliflower and broccoli.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish. Cover with a mixture of the celery soup and Cheez Whiz or cheese soup. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In a large stock pot, add the seasonings to the water and bring to a boil.
Add the sausage and boil, uncovered, 5 minutes. Add the corn and count 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and count 3 minutes.
(Don't wait for the liquid to return to a boil before timing corn and shrimp.)
Drain immediately and serve.
Serves 8.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Mix eggs, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Layer sausage and broccoli in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: rice krispies and cheese
directions: After mixing cheese and butter together, add the flour and Rice Krispies, blending well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: tenderloin of pork with apple-raisin gravy
directions: Season pork with salt, sage and pepper.
Roast, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple ring pickles
directions: Mix and pour over cucumbers.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Pour into a large pot; bring to a boil.
Pack cucumber in jars.
Pour hot liquid over them and seal.

title: sausage throw-together
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Add bell peppers, onion, tomatoes, mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste and mayonnaise; stir well.
Cover; cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender. Okay to add up to 1 cup water for extra gravy.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add onion; simmer until golden yellow. Add ground beef.
Stir, breaking up meat until lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a large casserole and bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: annie monsen's stuffed white fish
directions: Fillet your white fish.
Set aside.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter until onions are tender.
Use a large frypan.
Slowly add carrots, herbs, spices and lemon juice.
Add mushrooms and bread crumbs.
Add lightly beaten eggs and fold in. Take enough aluminum foil to wrap entire fish and place on a cookie sheet.
Butter the area where your fish will lay.
Place 1 fillet (skin down) and salt and pepper, if you want.
Dot with butter and bring foil up around fish.
Cover with stuffing.
Place other fillet on top.
Wrap lightly and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chocolate crinkles(cookies)
directions: Mix granulated sugar, oil, vanilla, and melted chocolate.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
(Dough will harden.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in large pot.
Add flour and stir well.
Add chicken broth, chicken soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vegetable mix and chicken. Stir well and pour into large casserole dish. Pull biscuits apart and place on top.
Bake at 350°
until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Take a small handful of dough and roll thin, 6 to 8 inches wide. Put 1/2 cup cut up apples in center of dough, dab of butter in center and sprinkle cinnamon and 1/8 cup sugar.
Fold dough over top of apples. Paint with Crisco; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: 1st Part: Cook small package of broccoli with onion about 6 minutes.
Drain.
Salt to taste.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Make the night before.
Place bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together. Pour over pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli stuffing bake
directions: In bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Add stuffing, chicken, broccoli and celery; mix well.
Spread mixture in 3-quart, oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix first four ingredients and
set aside.
Mix sifted flour with salt and oleo and work with fingers like pie dough.
(I use food processor)
In blender, beat 6 eggs well with flavoring.
Add to dough mixture and then add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Knead dough and add more flour if needed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 8 or 9 balls.
Roll each ball of dough out in confectionary sugar in a round like pie crust.
Cut into 8 wedges. On each wedge place 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Roll up and form into crescent shape.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cool lime pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Add limeade and food coloring if desired.
Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Garnish with kiwi. Add remaining whipped topping.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: moussaka (greek)
directions: Fry eggplant and potato slices separately in oil.
Set aside. Fry chopped onion in 3 sticks of margarine.
Add hamburger meat, salt, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook milk, 1/2 stick margarine and flour in double boiler until thick.
Add onion, pimento, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook lima beans.
Arrange limas in bottom of dish; add corn.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine with 1 1/2 to 2 cups stuffing, and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until tender; drain.
Set aside and keep warm.
Combine chicken and 1/4 of the dressing in nonstick skillet over medium high heat.
Saute chicken 2 minutes, until lightly browned.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing. Cover and simmer 7-9 minutes until vegetables are crisp tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: hot hors d'oeuvres
directions: Assemble as listed and broil until golden.

title: hoosier peanut bars
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Blend in alternately dry ingredients and cold water.
Press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over dough and press in gently. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add brown sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread over dough.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Pour cream over bottom of deep pie plate or small square cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts (if desired).
Cut biscuits into fourths and drop on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert onto plate and serve warm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix crackers, eggs and milk.
Mixture should have thick creamy consistency.
Add butter, pepper and corn.
Pour into greased (with butter) 9 x 9 pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until firm and brown on top.
Serves 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Microwave until bubbly or bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix oleo, flour and powdered sugar; press into a round pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix together cream cheese, milk, Cool Whip, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Cook strawberries, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Cool completely.
Spread over cream cheese filling. Refrigerate.
Serve.

title: peach crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Scald milk.
Put sugar, salt and Crisco into bowl.
Pour hot liquid over.
Stir and cool to warm. Soften yeast in warm water and add to ingredients.
Add about 2 cups of flour to mixture and stir.
Add eggs.
Beat mixture well.
Add more flour to make a dough that is soft but stiff enough to handle on board.

title: lemon-lime slaw salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until clear. Stir in 1 cup cold water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: monte criso au gratin
directions: Make 6 ham sandwiches.
Dip in the beaten eggs and fry in hot oil on a griddle.

title: holiday cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and melted butter in bowl; mix well.
Press into a spring-form pan.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, blend sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Blend well. Spoon on waxed paper.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add raisins, if desired.
Mix well and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: gourmet french toast
directions: In shallow dish (a pie pan works well), blend the eggs, milk, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Preheat grill or pan to temperature for pancakes.
Dip each piece of bread in mixture, about 3 seconds on each side, and place on grill.
Cook approximately 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.

title: great chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer in large pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: herb-rice mix
directions: Divide rice and bouillon granules into 4 gift packages; set aside.
Combine parsley flakes and remaining ingredients; stir and divide among gift packages.
Seal.
Include recipe with packages. Yield:
4 packages.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat at low speed just until blended.
Do not overbeat or cake will collapse.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° (clean toothpick).
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: cheesy macaroni salad
directions: Place macaroni in bowl and add cheese; mix together.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix together onion, both peppers, mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Add parsley and lemon juice; season well.
Mix again.
Pour over macaroni and cheese and mix to combine.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: rice-stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling salted water to cover; drain.
Set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix ingredients together and let gel.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Arrange 4 noodles in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Blend in cream cheese. Stir in cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Spread one-half of the mixture over the noodles. Combine soup, milk and wine in bowl.
Stir in shrimp and crabmeat.
Spread one-half of mixture over cottage cheese layer.
Repeat layers again. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with the shredded sharp cheese and bake an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken casserole(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix soups and tomatoes in saucepan. Add cheese and cook slowly until melted. Layer Doritos, chicken and cheese mixture. Top with crumbled Doritos and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: elaina's rice
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° until heated through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish (makes two large helpings).
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell until golden brown.
Let cool in a bowl.
Melt cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix. Add sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip; fill in pie shell.
Put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Put fruit topping on and serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese, marshmallow cream and yogurt.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.
"You can use low-fat yogurt."

title: beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat in large pan, then add peeled vegetables. Season to taste.
Add about a quart of water; bring to a boil, then let simmer until vegetables are done.
Serve with green salad and cornbread.

title: the reuben
directions: Spread bread with dressing on each of 12 bread slices. Arrange 1 cheese slice, 2 teaspoons of sauerkraut and 2 slices corned beef.
Stack the bread to make 6 sandwiches.
Cover with remaining bread slices.
Secure with picks.
Spread outside surfaces with butter and grill until cheese is melted and heated thoroughly.
Cut diagonally into three pieces.
Serve with French fried potatoes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Tear cake into chunks.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour pineapple and juice into pudding (use only 1 can juice).
Pour over cake.
Slice banana on top of pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: extra good frosting
directions: Add instant pudding mix to crushed pineapple. Do not drain pineapple.
Mix well and add Cool Whip.
Put on a 9 x 13-inch white or yellow cake.
Keep chilled.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Arrange vegetables in a 3-quart dish.
Place squash and onion on bottom and mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cut butter into patties and place on top.
Cover.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put ingredients in mixing bowl except shredded zucchini.
Beat with mixer until moistened.
Add zucchini; blend well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Blend mustard and jelly in blender.
Heat in a saucepan until boiling.
Cut wieners in pieces and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and place in sauce.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water; add milk and mix.
Cook for 2 or 3 minutes, then add vanilla and sweetener.
Spread on small foil pie pan or plate.
Chill.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Form into egg shaped balls and then roll lightly in pudding powder or chopped nuts.

title: cherry salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat until it boils, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Add cherries, walnuts and bananas; chill.

title: spiced punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
Put sugar in tea strainer (or if mixed loose, strain later) and allow to simmer in the juices for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and pumpkin.
Mix in baking mix and spices.
Blend in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake until set at 350°, for 50 to 55 minutes.
Refrigerate leftover pie.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over wings.
Marinate overnight.
Drain off marinade.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn meal.
Shape into patties and roll in corn meal and fry in hot oil, turning once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with 1 cup crushed crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Stir and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Melt Butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix with butter. Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix and beat with electric mixer for 2 to 3 minutes. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with fresh strawberries, bananas, apple slices, melon, kiwi fruit, etc.

title: pie crusts
directions: Blend flour, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until particles are size of peas.
Beat egg and stir in vinegar and water and blend.
Divide into 4 balls and put each in a Ziploc bag and freeze until you want to use.
Thaw and roll out and use as your recipe calls for.

title: olive sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread.
Cut in desired size.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Add next three ingredients. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed, then add the last two ingredients.
Beat two more minutes.
Pour batter into two 9-inch round pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Crumble raw ground beef into water; do not brown.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 3 hours.
Remove garlic toe and bay leaves.

title: creamy chicken broccoli noodles
directions: Prepare Ramen noodles according to package directions.
Add seasoning packets.
Drain off most of liquid. Stir in mushroom soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through. Yields 4 servings.

title: hot cider
directions: Melt red hots in cider. Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add corn, oleo, salt and milk.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add sugar until creamy.
Stir pecans and flour into butter mixture.
Roll dough into small balls. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll while hot in powdered sugar.
When cool, roll again.
(These burn very easily, so check them while baking.)

title: best chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Add all ingredients, except nuts.
Place in baking pan.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then eat it.

title: nancy's fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients with exception of nuts.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch (or larger) pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook
noodles.	 Saute	meat
until
browned.
Stir
in sauce, onion
and	seasonings.
Simmer.
Spread 1/3 meat sauce in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add half noodles, laying side by side over sauce. Combine
cottage
cheese and egg.
Place 1/2 over noodles.	Cover with 1/2 pizza cheese and 1/2 Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers.
Top with
last
meat sauce mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ruby's sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add sour cream and flavorings; beat well.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add to the first mixture; mix. Grease pan and bake in a moderate oven, about 350°, for approximately one hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: candied yams
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain off about 1/2 of liquid from canned yams.
Pour yams and remaining liquid into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the next five ingredients and then top with marshmallows.
Bake for 1 hour, or until nice and bubbly.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring butter and water to boiling point in saucepan.
Combine flour and salt, add to water.
Mix well.
Cook stirring constantly, until mixture forms smooth, compact mass.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 35 min. or until thoroughly browned and set. Cool.
Make slit with sharp knife near bottom of puff.
Fill with vanilla pudding and frost.

title: tuna mac and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Cover and heat for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Heat 10 minutes longer or until mixture is heated through and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Lightly grease 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle chicken, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie pan. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirt cake dessert
directions: Crumble cookies in a blender until fine consistency (until it looks like dirt).
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar in a bowl.
Mix pudding and milk in a bowl and let stand.
Layer in a flowerpot the dirt, pudding, dirt, pudding and dirt.
Top with flowers to give appearance of plant.

title: buttermilk drop cookies
directions: Note:
All measurements are level; use measuring cup only.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except for the lime juice. Add the lime juice immediately before serving.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Spread batter on cookie sheet.
Cut the surface of batter with a knife to make 35 squares.
Spoon pie filling on top of squares.
Batter will puff up around pie fillings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cut 35 squares and sprinkle with powdered (10x) sugar.

title: cheesy biscuit dinner
directions: Separate dough into ten biscuits.
Press or roll each into a 4-inch circle.
Combine cream cheese and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese with 1 tablespoon onion.
Mix.
Blend well.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon mixture onto center of each biscuit.
Fold dough in half over filling.
Press edges with fork to seal.
In a skillet, brown beef with remaining onion soup mix; drain.
Stir in soup, remaining Cheddar cheese and eggs; heat until hot and bubbly, stirring quickly to keep eggs from cooking up separately.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; arrange filled biscuits in hot meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and fruit cocktail.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Serve cold.

title: ham souffle
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices (butter each slice of bread).
Put 1 slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Put a layer of cubed ham on top of bread slices and cheese.
Repeat layering.
Beat the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over ham and bread.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Place pan on a cookie sheet with water in bottom of cookie sheet.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Make your pudding with milk; blend in butter, cream cheese, sugar and, last, the Cool Whip.
Crunch cookies in blender about 5 at a time.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then add to sugar mixture.
Pour into 1-quart Ziploc bag and freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Add 1 (2 liter) 7-Up per 2-quarts. Yield: 40 to 50 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: mrs. cade's vegetable pie
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add basil, garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet.
Briefly saute zucchini, squash and tomatoes and combine with onions and mushrooms.
Drain well!
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate which has been lined with puff pastry.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar, then add eggs and pumpkin.
Sift spices with flour and add to pumpkin mixture; blend.
Add water, raisins and nuts.
Blend.
Pour into 2 greased pans; fill only half pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: squash souffle
directions: Note:
You can add 4 teaspoons diet oleo and add 1/2 fat selection, but it is not necessary.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuit pieces in cinnamon-sugar mixture until well coated.
Place in a Bundt cake pan.
Pour melted butter, nuts and brown sugar mixture over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini and rice casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer rice, zucchini, mushrooms, onions and cottage cheese.
Season with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic salt.
Pour can of soup over entire casserole and add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Must be Minute rice.)

title: chop suey cake - cousin dot
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peaches 'n cream smoothie
directions: Place peach, milk and ice milk in a blender jar or shake maker.
Blend for 15 seconds.
Add yogurt and blend for 10 seconds longer.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chalupa
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat.
Add onions, hash browns, cumin, garlic salt, water and simmer covered on medium heat.
In a different pan add oil.
On high heat, fry flour
tortillas pushing air pockets out until lightly brown.
Place tortilla on plate. Then while you are frying the tortillas heat beans in separate pan on low heat stirring constantly for 5 - 10 minutes.
After beans are cooked, spread a spoonful on tortilla.
Add 3 - 5 Tbsp. of beef on top of beans.
Add lettuce, cheese, sauce and salt. Serves 6 - 8.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, 3/4 c. sugar, and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Reserve 1/2 c. of batter.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cream milk and cream cheese.
Dissolve gelatine and Jell-O in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add sugar to can of pineapple and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and gelatine mixture.
Mix well.
Add cream cheese mix to pineapple mixture.
Place mixture in very large container.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into large Bundt pan.
Chill.
To serve, remove from pan and slice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook mixture of sugar, water, vinegar and flour until clear. After mixture has cooled, add 3/4 cup mayonnaise and mustard. Pour over broccoli, bacon and onion.
Dressing can also be used for Spanish salad.

title: mint chocolate brownies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs together. Add flour, vanilla, salt and syrup. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13 sprayed pan. Cool. Mix 1/2 c. oleo, creme de mint and powdered sugar. Spread over brownies.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Knead out on floured board. Roll or cut biscuits.
Place in pan with a little shortening melted in it.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: Melt butter.
Add spices.
Pour over popcorn, nuts and potato stick mixture.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Add broccoli; stir until broccoli is broken up. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Spread on crackers or party rye bread.
Enjoy!

title: mrs. mcnutt's congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows and dissolve.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill and whip, then add fruit cocktail, pineapple, cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: party sandwiches
directions: After browning beef and sausage, put in the crock-pot.
Add Velveeta cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat all together. Serve on party rye bread (small squares).

title: instant brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Heat and serve.
(Can also be cooked in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.)

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Finely chop the chicken.
In a bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and dry sherry or sake; set aside.
In a large saucepan, bring water and bouillon granules to boiling.
Stir in the chicken mixture, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, vinegar and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Slice the fresh bean curd into 1 1/2 x 1/4-inch strips; add to the soup.

title: tempura(deep fried)
directions: Serve with soy sauce.

title: indian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, stirring with spoon.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 -inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost warm.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Boil chicken in saucepan in pineapple juice, plus juice from pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges.
Salt and pepper chicken and add celery before boiling.
When done, debone and chill.
Combine lettuce, cucumber, carrots, oranges, pineapple, strawberries and tomatoes in large bowl.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Serve with crackers or Honey-Yogurt Dressing.

title: * marinated carrots *
directions: Heat cooked carrots and drain.
Cook over ingredients over slow heat about 20 minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Let set in refrigerator a couple of days before serving.
This is easy to mix at home and take along on campouts.

title: yeast spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast and lukewarm water and set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg in center of bowl of dry ingredients. Add yeast mixture next then melted shortening.
Mix well and store in refrigerator (preferably overnight) to let dough rise, cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Use dough as needed.

title: crispy snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well; set aside.
Combine margarine and next 5 ingredients in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until margarine melts.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture. Sprinkle with cheese; toss well.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crisp, stirring occasionally.
Cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 5 cups; 103 calories (24% from fat) per 1/2 cup serving, fat 2.7 g, cholesterol 1 mg, sodium 219 mg.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper in skillet.
In another pan, add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Combine these two mixtures in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chunky chicken vegetable noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, tomato sauce and vegetables. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Stir in soup mix and chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Makes about 5 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer all vegetables together in olive oil for about 20 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Layer vegetables, then tomatoes alternating.
Sprinkle cheese, then crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In a heavy saucepan, thoroughly mix cornstarch with sugar. Add milk and stir into sugar until dissolved.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Turn heat to low and continue stirring while it boils, for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: fried rice with bacon
directions: Prepare rice.
In wok or skillet, saute bacon. Drain on paper and cut into pieces.
In 1/4 cup drippings, saute mushrooms and onions until onions are glassy.
Add rice.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pull rice to sides.
In middle, pour egg and scramble. Add water chestnuts, bacon and soy sauce.
Stir-fry until all is warm and mixed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Coarsely crush 4 cups cereal.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Mix in sugar and dates.
Pour in large skillet; stir constantly over low heat 5 minutes or until dates are soft and mixture is thick. Stir in nuts, vanilla, salt and crushed cereal.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool.
Roll 1 1/2 cups cereal into fine crumbs.
Drop cooled date mixture from teaspoon onto crumbs.
Roll into balls. Makes 3 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Garnish with lemon or orange.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: yeast cornbread
directions: Scald milk; stir in salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water into large bowl; sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in milk mixture, eggs, flour and cornmeal. Beat until well mixed about 2 minutes.
Batter will be very stiff.
Pour into two greased 8-inch round cake pans or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: celia's baked haddock
directions: Use 2 containers.
Put your milk in one and bread crumbs in another.
Roll haddock in milk first, then roll haddock in the bread crumbs next.
In bottom of a buttered 9 x 9-inch cake pan, place haddock.
Pour the rest of your butter on the top of your haddock.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until fish is flaky and pulls apart easily with a fork.

title: meat loaf-cheeseburgers
directions: Mix together hamburger
and
onion, put in enough sauce to flavor; do not make it
too
runny.
Shape
and
fry
in
a skillet over medium to
high
heat
until brown on both sides. When almost done put remaining sauce on top of each hamburger, with a slice of cheese;
cover
with
lid and let cheese melt, then serve.

title: baked jumbo shrimp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Peel shrimp.
Make a shallow cut lengthwise down back of each shrimp; wash out vein.
Pour oil into rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place shrimp in oil. Sprinkle with parsley, onions and garlic.
Pour broth and lemon juice over shrimp.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes or until shrimp are done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Make a white sauce from butter, flour, milk,
salt and pepper.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients as listed (add eggs one at a time).
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased tube pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed cornflakes.
Line 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish with cornflake mixture, reserving some for the top. Place cabbage in dish and pour ingredients over cabbage.
Put buttered cornflakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco beef bake
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Add soup, salsa, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and tortillas.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Serves 4.

title: rollup deer
directions: Cut steak into 2 inch squares and tenderize with mallet.
Dip steak in sauce and roll up.
Wrap 1/2 strip of bacon around steak and hold together with toothpick.
Cook on grill until bacon is done.

title: pecan pie #4
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add syrup, pecans and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: robin's chicken salad
directions: Cut cooled chicken into strips.
Add fruit and nuts.
Add mayonnaise slowly; stir gently until chicken mixture is thoroughly coated.
Chill.
Can prepare the day before, leaving out bananas until ready to serve.
Spoon salad on large lettuce leaf.
Garnish with extra almonds.
My all time favorite recipe!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian tuna noodle casserole
directions: Drain tuna.
Use 3 tablespoons oil to cook celery and onion until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic, oregano, basil and fennel.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles.
Lightly grease 2-quart casserole.
Layer half noodles. Top with half tuna mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased floured pan.
Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: beef oriental casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and celery; add other ingredients.
Last, add and toss in sprouts.
Bake at 350°, covered for 1/2 hour; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party aspic
directions: Heat gelatin and beef broth.
When boiling, pour over and stir until lemon jello is dissolved.
Add tomato soup, tomato salsa and V-8.
Mix and chill until firm.
Unmold on platter.
Garnish with greens.
Serve with dressing made of cream cheese, Blue cheese and mayonnaise.
Add milk to soften to desired consistency.
If you are watching salt intake, use low sodium V-8.

title: favorite icing
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cover and refrigerate in a mixing bowl.
Beat butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add chilled milk and flour mixture; beat (with electric beater) for 10 minutes.
Frost cooled cake. Yields 12 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 400° until light brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may want to freeze half of this before baking.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1/3 cup milk and stir well.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Then add 1/3 cup milk.
In a kettle, combine cocoa and part of remaining milk and mix well. Add remaining milk.
Heat to warm, stirring constantly, and then pour this mixture into sugar mixture.
Stir well and pour back into the kettle.
Cook until thick.
Then add vanilla and butter and stir well.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: orange and lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, orange juice and mandarin oranges.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make pudding with 1 cup milk.
Combine with Cool Whip. Spread over set jello and let cool in refrigerator.

title: beef stew
directions: Put everything in a casserole and bake very slowly 3 hours or more---can also be done in a crockpot.

title: bacon pot roast
directions: Fry bacon in large Dutch oven until crisp.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Sprinkle roast with lemon pepper marinade.
Brown roast on all sides in hot bacon drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture over roast.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until roast is tender.
Remove roast to warm platter; sprinkle with bacon.
Serve roast with pan drippings. Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic and mushrooms in skillet.
Mix all ingredients except sour cream/flour.
Cook in crock pot on low 6 - 8 hours or on high 3 hours.
Stir in sour cream 1 hour before serving.

title: suzanne's fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook onion in butter, then mix all other ingredients together, except cornflakes.
Blend well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cornflakes if desired.

title: sue gander's bread recipe
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large bowl and let cool.
Mix warm water and yeast in measuring cup.
Sprinkle a little salt and sugar with this; makes it work better.
(Sue Frances said, "Do the dishes while above is cooling.")
Put yeast water in Crisco water.
Put in 2 cups flour and mix with electric mixer.
Keep adding flour until right consistency for dough.
(Recipe says 7 to 8 cups but Sue Frances said it does not take that much, all depends on the weather.)
Put on biscuit board and knead until not sticky.
Wash large bowl and grease it and put dough back in to rise to double bulk, usually 2 or 3 hours.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes. (Knead if sticky adding more flour, Sue Frances said she seldom had to do this.)
Grease two loaf pans.
Shape into 2 loaves and put in pans.
Let rise until double in bulk, 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven or until brown.
Take out and put butter on top and put back in oven with heat off for a few minutes.

title: best ever chicken salad
directions: Toast almonds in oven for 5 minutes at 350°.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and vinegar; add to chicken, black olives, celery and almonds.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold together.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice until tender and drain.
Fry onions and pepper, using oil or butter.
Add to rice.
Then add tomato paste and salt to taste and let simmer until soft.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and soda.
Add egg, then fruit cocktail.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Real good if made the day before.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender or follow directions on box.
Melt cheese, oleo and flour in a saucepan over low heat.
Add milk until thickened.
Add a pinch of pepper, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour half the macaroni in a casserole; then half of cheese mixture.
Do so until all ingredients are layered. Top with 2 1/2 tablespoons of bread crumbs.
Cook in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Cream butter and sugars well; add egg, flour and vanilla and beat well.
Add peanut butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until transparent and tender. Add vegetables, cover and steam for a few minutes until crisp but tender. Stir in tomato sauce, water, oregano and basil. Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler until cheese is bubbly. Cut each with pizza cutter into fourths.

title: toffee wafers
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cook on stove for a few minutes (until it boils).
Line the bottom of a cake pan with graham crackers and pour caramelized mixture over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt milk chocolate and pour over the whole thing, smoothing evenly.
Let cook and cut or break into pieces to serve.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat until lukewarm cottage cheese, sugar, minced onion, dill seed, butter, salt and soda.
Add unbeaten egg and yeast mixture.
Mix in to form a stiff dough, bread flour.
Let mixture rise in a warm place until it has doubled in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir the dough down.
Turn into a well-greased casserole dish or two loaf pans.
Let rise in a warm place for 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Spread butter and salt on top after removing from oven.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Place in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken.
Put in casserole; cover with broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top. Bake 15 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage balls
directions: Soak bread in orange juice and syrup. Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Blend in sausage, pecans and parsley. Form into 1-inch balls.
Fry over low heat turning occasionally for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in microwave.
Add peanut butter and stir until well mixed.
Add shoestring potatoes.
Stir until well coated.
Drop on wax paper and let sit until hard.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift together.
Beat egg whites and salt. When foamy, add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff.
Add remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until well blended.
Add flavoring.
Sift 1/4 cup flour and sugar over mixture.
Fold in lightly.
Repeat until all is used.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Cut batter with knife to remove air bubbles.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 50 minutes. Remove and invert pan 1/2 hour.
Let cool 2 hours before icing.

title: homemade chicken stock
directions: Use enough cold water to cover everything by at least 2 inches. Don't peel anything.
Wash vegetables and cut into big hunks.
Stud unpeeled onion with cloves and dump everything into a large stockpot.
Cover partially; turn the fire on low and forget it for 6 hours.
When it's done, turn off the fire and let cool a bit. Line colander with cheesecloth; pour stock through cheesecloth into a big pot.
Let cool to room temperature before you jar it up.
Use gravy separator to defat stock.
I freeze 2 ice cube trays with broth and store cubes in plastic bag for when I need small amounts of stock.
I do not salt this.
That way, I can adjust salt when cooking.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut up nuts and fruits. Sprinkle with flour to keep from sticking together.
Mix cake mix, applesauce, eggs, salt and flavoring.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Bake in 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: barbecued meat
directions: In saucepan, blend last 5 ingredients.
Heat.
Add meat until warm.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil first three ingredients together for five minutes.
Make tea using 8 tea bags to six cups water.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon cloves and 1 teaspoon cinnamon to tea and mix with the juices.
Keep hot while serving.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese.
Add egg yolk, sugar and milk. Beat well.
Mix powder and flour.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Drop onto cookie sheet, one teaspoon at a time (1/2 to 3/4-inch circle). Press with thumb and fill with jelly.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: grilled swordfish steaks
directions: Preheat broiler or grill.
In a small bowl, combine butter, chili powder and chives. Put a small amount of seasoned butter on the top side of each steak.
Grill or broil for about 5 minutes, then turn steaks and put seasoned butter on other side (don't use all of butter).
Grill or broil 5 minutes more, then use remaining butter on top of the grilled fish. Serve hot.

title: bran nut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except the pecans.
Mix until smooth, then add pecans.
Spoon mixture into cupcake holders.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: kit-kat bars
directions: Place a layer of Waverly or Club crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 cup margarine or butter in a saucepan. Add the brown sugar and white sugar.
Mix. Add the milk and mix. Add the graham cracker crumbs gradually.
Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes. Stir or it may burn.
Spread half of that mixture on the layer of crackers.
Lay on another layer of crackers using a different pattern (this will keep them from falling apart when cut).
Spread the rest of the mixture on that layer.
Lay on another layer of crackers, using original pattern.
Melt the butterscotch chips and chocolate chips. Add the peanut butter. Melt together and mix well.
Spread over top.
Cool completely. (Perhaps refrigerate for 1 hour.)
Cut and enjoy.

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and all other ingredients slowly. Bake in a greased pie pan at 325° for 35 minutes. When cool, cover with Cool Whip.

title: curry chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in melted butter; remove from pan.
Add onions and apples; saute until onions are tender.
Sprinkle with curry powder and flour.
Cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Stir in broth; bring to a boil.
Add chicken; cover and cook over low heat for 40 minutes, or until tender.
If sauce is too thick, add more broth.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, mix in pineapple, pepper, 1/2 of the nuts, salt and onion.
Chill overnight. Form into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: grandma's macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Place cooked macaroni in bottom of baking dish.
Mix into this, the cubed sharp cheese.
Slice onions and green peppers.
Layer over macaroni.
Place ground beef on top of onions and green peppers.
Pour tomatoes and tomato juice over the meat.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours; cover with foil.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix as directed.
Crumble.
Put half in layer, half of chopped pepper, half chopped onion and half of bacon (crumbled).
Put pickle juice in mayonnaise and blend.
Put half on mixture, then repeat layers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Mix 5 tablespoons self-rising flour and 5 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle over peaches.
Mix 1 cup self-rising flour, milk and margarine and spread over dry mixture and peaches.
Combine 1 cup sugar and water and pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar to egg whites, then vanilla, salt and baking powder. Fold in crackers and nuts. Pour into a buttered pie pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Pour into greased pan to cool.
Cut in squares.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, mix soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, salt, red pepper and ginger.
Heat oil in wok or high-sided frying pan. Briefly fry cashews; remove and add more oil if needed.
Fry chicken and remove.
Add remaining vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sauce and all previously fried ingredients.
Stir and fry another 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with white or fried rice.

title: ranch broccoli pasta salad - light
directions: In a large bowl, combine the pasta, broccoli and onion. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, salad dressing mix and salt. Add to pasta mixture; toss to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in bacon. Yield: 12 servings.

title: just cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until fluffy, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Keep a day or 2 before using.
Will freeze well.

title: seafood casserole(can be halved)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with crushed crumbs (I use crackers).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces, cook and cool.
Mix in chopped vegetables, dressing and salad supreme.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: fiesta cheese cake
directions: Combine chips and butter and press in bottom of greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in shredded cheese, chilies and peppers.
Pour in pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Spread with sour cream and chill.
Arrange remaining ingredients on top and place on bed of fresh cilantro. Serve with tortilla chips.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: easy macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; put in a large bowl to cool.
If a bigger batch is needed, double amounts of whatever.
After cooled, add mayonnaise, cheese, crazy salt and whatever else you want to add. Mix well and cool.
Decorate top with small amount of parsley. This goes well with any kind of meat.

title: buttermilk egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on open pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: meatball minestrone
directions: Prepare mini meatballs.
Mix remaining ingredients except spaghetti and zucchini in Dutch oven; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; stir in meatballs.
Heat to boiling; stir in spaghetti and zucchini.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti and zucchini are tender.
Sprinkle each serving with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: big mama's brittles
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch pan with foil.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom with single layer of crackers.
Heat butter and sugar to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Place in oven until crackers rise, about 2 minutes.
Remove and top with chocolate chips.
Spread after melting.
Add nuts to top. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate passion trifle
directions: Prepare brownies as directed.
Sprinkle warm baked brownies with 1 tablespoon of the coffee liqueur.
Cool in pan; cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with a wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let mixture stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in the remaining 1 tablespoon of coffee liqueur and 2 cups of the Cool Whip until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Reserve a few raspberries and pecans for garnish.
Layer 1/2 the brownies, remaining raspberries, 1/2 chopped Heath bars, pecans and 1/2 pudding mixture in a 2-quart glass bowl (or trifle bowl).
Repeat layers.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and raspberries. Refrigerate.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil cauliflower until almost tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain about 10 minutes.
Chop cauliflower, eggs, celery, onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together; add Miracle Whip or mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Combine eggs, cottage cheese, ricotta cheese and Italian seasoning in a medium bowl.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in hot butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper; add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir one more minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in spinach, carrot and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.

title: marinade sauce for beef
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Great for flank steak or shish-kabobs.

title: no bake chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan or spray sides and bottom; line with graham crackers (make them fit).
Beat pudding with milk and add whipped topping.
Pour 1/2 pudding over graham crackers, top with graham crackers, top with second 1/2 of pudding.
Cover with another layer of crackers (this makes 3rd layer).
Put frosting in micro for 30 seconds or until soft and spread on dessert.
This must set in refrigerator for 10 hours.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan the white sugar, oleo and milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, cocoa, peanut butter and Minute oats.
Stir together.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper and cool.

title: best ever salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve with mayonnaise on lettuce leaf.
This salad is good with chicken or ham.
The horseradish may be omitted, but it makes it good and different.!

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Chill until ready to use.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, one-half butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese and stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twist and parsley if desired.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: canadian sheperd's pie
directions: Fry hamburg until the red is gone.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat for 2nd layer. Bake in 300° oven until hot through (about 20 minutes).
Garnish with a salad, dessert and drink.
Serves 4.

title: reuben turnovers
directions: Thaw dough and roll out to a 12 inch square.
Cut into 9 (4-inch) squares.
Cut cheese and meat into triangles.
Layer meat, pickles and cheese on each square of dough.
Fold and pinch edges making a turnover.
Split top for steam.
Bake on greased baking sheet in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: creamy crab dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave margarine 45 seconds on High.
Add onion, garlic and parsley.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 3 minutes on High. Add cheese cubes and microwave one minute on High, stirring once. Stir in Worcestershire, Tabasco and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in crabmeat.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High until thoroughly heated.
Serve warm on toast points or with bland crackers.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and milk for 1 minute.
Pour over the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt oleo in casserole or baking dish.
Mix together corn, eggs, sour cream and corn muffin mix.
Pour mixture in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: boston cooler
directions: Slice the cantaloupe in half.
Remove the seeds with a tablespoon.
Fill the hollow of each melon half with ice cream. Garnish each serving with a cherry.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Chop onion and cook in water over medium heat until tender.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, margarine, eggs and 1/2 of Town House crackers.
Mix well and pour in baking dish.
Top with remaining crackers, crumbled, and bake in microwave for 10 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Gradually add juice.
Add to pineapple in 2-quart casserole.
Put cheese on top, then add crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts. Put in a pizza pan and bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: rio grande supper
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onion and bell pepper. Cook until tender. Stir in corn, Cheez Whiz, barbecue sauce and chili powder. Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Top with corn chips if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in buttermilk, soda, sugar, salt, shortening and half of flour.
Add rest of flour.
Mix with hands.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Roll out flat and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise until double, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be made into cinnamon rolls.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Whip the Dream Whip and milk and mix all together.
Top with pineapple and put in graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.

title: rocky road fudge bars
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat oleo and sugars together until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to oleo mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely. Store in airtight container.
Bake at 350°.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: mock hollandaise sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small nonstick saucepan.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Serve over broccoli or asparagus. Yields 4 servings (2 tablespoons each).
Has 25 calories, less than 1 g fat.

title: turkey-popcorn dressing
directions: Prepare turkey for roasting.
Butter cavity well.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stuff with 6 big cupfuls of unpopped popcorn.
Sew up tight.
Put in oven at 500°.
Get out of kitchen and let her go. When the popping corn busts the stitches, then you'll know it's done.
Remove from oven with broom and shovel.
Use for turkey flavored popcorn snack or dispose of properly.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in bottle of liquid smoke overnight.
Cook next morning on lowest setting of oven for about 8 hours or until it pulls apart with a fork.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaf.
Chop chicken into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Reserve 1/4 cup broth; cook spaghetti in remaining broth and drain.
Saute onion, celery, pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Add to spaghetti.
Combine mushroom soup and 1/4 cup broth and stir into spaghetti mixture.
Add tomatoes and chicken; mix well.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Bake 2 pie crusts and let cool.
Cook first 3 ingredients until it thickens.
Let cool slightly.
Add coconut and nuts; mix well.
Line bottom of crusts with sliced bananas.
Put a layer of pineapple filling over bananas.
Serve Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add to taco seasoning, salsa and refried beans.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with sour cream and olives. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips. (Corn chips are good!)

title: texas cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour into bowl containing the flour, sugar, egg, sour milk, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well and pour into large pan.
The thinner it is the better the cake.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: angel food cake filling
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and juice.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread onto angel food cake.

title: corn bread dressing with chicken
directions: Cook, uncovered, first 4 ingredients in 4 quarts of water until done, but still firm.
Bone chicken; save skin, bones and vegetables and reboil for additional stock if needed.
Mix remaining ingredients well and add deboned chicken.
Mixture will be a little on soupy side.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Will make 2 roasting pans filled.
I make one and put remaining dressing in freezer bag for future use or it is good to share with family members.

title: anne's cheesecake
directions: First Layer:
Crush graham crackers and mix with 1/4 cup sugar, chopped walnuts, butter and cinnamon.
Press into pan and up the sides of the spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Crush crackers with melted margarine.
Put over top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream eggs, margarine, oil, sugar, vanilla and buttermilk. Add all dry ingredients.
Add zucchini last.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
I added nuts and left out the cloves.

title: play dough
directions: Stir and cook for 60 seconds or until dough balls up.
Put on wax paper and cool, then make a ball.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, measure and sift with the spices and cocoa.
Add nuts, raisins and jam.
Cream shortening and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with the milk.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven.
Makes 3 layers. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: port medallions with spinach and tomatoes
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large nonreactive skillet.
Add the Prosciutto and garlic; cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the garlic is golden, about 4 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.

title: mom flowers' potato cakes
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, egg and flour together until well mixed. Make sure the mixture is not syrupy.
Deep fry on high until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: green and white salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: mother's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, milk and flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Immediately turn out upside down on a plate.
Serve warm.

title: mexican noodle bake
directions: Boil macaroni; brown the ground beef.
Add all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Cook in 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes or until well heated.

title: demi-pound cake
directions: Mix egg whites until stiff.
Set aside. Add egg yolks and butter together.
Mix well. Add sugar and mix well.
Gradually add flour alternately with milk. Beat about 4 or 5 minutes.
Fold stiff egg whites into mixture.
Put into greased angel food pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Tube pan.)

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 11 x 16-inch pan.
Sift sugar and flour together in large bowl; set aside.
In saucepan, mix oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil; pour over sugar-flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into pan. Bake for 20 minutes.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and boiling water and let set until rest of batter is mixed.
Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Add oatmeal and water mixture to the above ingredients.
Mix well and bake in loaf pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: parisian soup
directions: Cook frozen veggies in 3 cup of water until tender.
Keep all liquid.
Saut onions and celery in butter.
Add bouillon cubes; add flour to thicken.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until ready to eat.
Good next day also.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done, debone and dice.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add vegetables (do not drain) and soup.
Mix and salt.
Top with biscuits; brush with butter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes (until brown).

title: quick pineapple pie
directions: In a large bowl, put pineapple, sour cream, dry pudding mix and sugar.
Mix all together by hand;
put into baked pastry shell or graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Can serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
With mixer on low, mix together cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly. Press into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk and 2 eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, then chill for several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ginger cookie
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs, then dry ingredients, molasses and vanilla. This is a double recipe.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Make into a ball and mash down with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yumasetta
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato soup, salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Simmer; boil and drain noodles.
Add chicken soup to noodles.
Put noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ground beef mixture; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind or chop vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Cover with foil.

title: sticky buns
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
In large bowl, combine sugar, salt and butter; add scalded milk.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Blend by mixer for 2 minutes.
Add egg and yeast mixture.
Beat on medium speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
With spoon, blend in remaining 2 cups flour; beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Turn out on floured board and knead 5 to 10 minutes; cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.

title: pepsi-cola cake
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and Pepsi to boil.
Pour over flour and beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows. Beat well.

title: yorkshire pudding(a "must" with roast beef)
directions: Twenty minutes before roast is done, make a batter by beating all the ingredients together.
Heat an empty square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) in the oven.
Remove roast.
Spoon off about 1/2 cup hot drippings.
Increase oven temperature to 425° (hot).
Return roast to oven.
Place hot drippings in heated pan.
Pour in batter. Bake 20 minutes.
Remove roast and continue baking pudding another 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut pudding in squares and serve immediately. Makes 6 to 9 Yorkshire puddings.

title: fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients. Put into greased 9-inch square pan.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add brown sugar, then white sugar. Cream well. Add eggs and vanilla and cream again. Add dry ingredients slowly, then chips, nuts and coconut. Dough will be stiff. We drop our cookies about the size of a walnut on a Pamed cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Share with friends.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds, crackers and bread. Spread mixture into a baking dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with water crackers or rye bread.

title: stuffed cabbage with sauerkraut
directions: In a saucepan bring water to a boil and add 1/4 teaspoon salt. Place cored, cleaned cabbage in water and cover, boiling gently until leaves are pliable, about 20 minutes.
Drain cabbage. Refresh under cold water and set aside.
In large bowl beat egg white with fork.
Add ground turkey, cooked rice, onions, 1/2 cup tomato juice, salt and pepper and mix with wooden spoon.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Carefully peel off 12 to 16 large cabbage leaves. Pat dry and trim away any thick rib or tough ends.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat filling in center of each leaf.
Fold sides over the filling and roll to encase filling.
Spread half the sauerkraut in a 3 to 4-quart roasting pan.
Arrange stuffed cabbage leaves in a single layer on top.
Top with remaining sauerkraut and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour remaining tomato juice over the pan of rolls.
Cover pan and transfer to oven and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is very tender.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Let them cool, then slice lengthwise and take white out, but don't break potato skin.
Put white of potato in bowl.
Add ingredients; mix well.
Fill the brown skin of potato with filling.
Spread grated cheese over top or green onions for looks.
Cook 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: enchiladas entomalodas
directions: Slightly fry tortilla in hot oil.
Put in baking dish (oil baking dish).
Add cheese, onions, green chiles and olives. Roll; continue until all tortillas are rolled.
Then spread sour cream all over enchiladas.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp rotel
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet; add onion, green pepper, garlic and pimientos.
Cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper and drained tomatoes and green chilies.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Run tap water on shrimp to dissolve ice crystals if using frozen shrimp. Then add drained shrimp to skillet mixture.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add reserved Ro-Tel juice if more liquid is needed. Either add rice and simmer 5 minutes or serve shrimp with platter of warm rice.
Serves 4.

title: mexicale chicken
directions: Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken and brown in non-stick pan.
Sprinkle chili powder, oregano, salt and pepper on chicken as it browns.
Pour off any excess fat.
Add onion, olives and hot water, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Remove chicken to bowl and separate from bones.
Prepare rice as directed on package (water, brown rice, salt and butter).
Blend 1/4 cup cold water and flour until smooth.
Add to broth in pan and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add walnuts to gravy along with chicken.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: no bake cocoa cookies with coconut
directions: Have all ingredients ready to work with.
Boil sugar, cocoa or brown sugar, Crisco and milk for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir constantly and remove from heat at once.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all to cover oats evenly.
Drop immediately by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together and pour over peaches in a pastry lined pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Can serve plain with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
When it starts to smoke, add dry shrimp and cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add garlic and shallots and cook 1 minute.
Deglace with white wine; add basil and tomatoes.
Cook two more minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cubes of butter until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over linguini.
Serves 8 people.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients.
Toss with dressing.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots lengthwise and then in 2-inch pieces.
Cook until just tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Drain.

title: banana bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Mix ingredients in order given. Bake in 1 large greased loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fry chik pilaf
directions: In a very large saucepan, melt margarine.
Break up vermicelli into 1 to 2-inch pieces and drop into margarine.
Stir until browned all over.
Add rice and stir.
Quickly add 5 to 6 cups of hot water and stir.
Add bouillon and soup base.
Cook about 20 minutes until rice is done, making sure it doesn't go dry and stir now and then.
Cut up Fry Chik into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces and add. (You may add a little of the Fry Chik juice, if desired.)
This should be cooked down enough to be just moist and not watery when rice is done.
Serve with a salad and a vegetable.
Will feed a large crowd.

title: reeses peanut butter cups
directions: Melt ingredients.
Use	1/2 of mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls
onto cupcake
papers,
then
add
a
tablespoon of softened creamy or
crunchy peanut butter on top of the chocolate and chill in refrigerator for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator and
put
a
tablespoonful
of	remaining warm chocolate mixture over it.	Chill until set.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put in large bowl the pineapple with juice.
Add the dry pudding; stir.
Add walnuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Decorate with cherries and walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pork medallions
directions: Combine olive oil and garlic in blender or food processor. Process, then add rosemary and whirl 1 minute more.
Arrange sliced tenderloins in 8 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Pour marinade over pork.
Stir and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
