Brown tenderloins in nonstick skillet for 2 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat, add lemon juice and cook, turning often, 3 to 5 minutes or until done. Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.
Elegant and easy!

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool.
Add all the ingredients, pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Chill.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Beat 1/2 cup sugar and margarine until smooth. Add next 5 ingredients and beat until smooth. Spray a 2-quart dish with Pam; spread batter in dish. Put berries or fruit over batter. Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over fruit. Pour water over top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zeppole
directions: Using cooking thermometer, heat vegetable oil in a deep saucepan to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together, except for powdered sugar.
Carefully add a tablespoon of mixture at a time to hot oil.
Within a minute, balls will form and puffs will turn golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 dozen Zeppole.

title: chocolate frostys
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix until smooth.

title: pork chops hawaiian
directions: Season pork chops; brown slowly.
Drain off drippings.
Mix together the applesauce, pineapple and nutmeg.
Pour over chops. Cover and let cook on low heat for about 30 minutes at about 325°.

title: fresh fruit with sour cream fluff
directions: Add pudding mix to cold milk in a mixing bowl.
Slowly beat with rotary beater until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in sour cream; chill thoroughly.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and milk in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat in oil and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into bran mixture only until combined.
Spoon into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together all above ingredients.
Place into 2 pie tins. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: crawfish bread
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, prepare roux by cooking the flour in the microwave

for 2 minutes. Stir and continue to microwave in 1 minute increments stopping to stir frequently to prevent roux from burning or getting hot spots, continuing this process until flour turns dark tan. If you burn and get hard black pieces, you can remove with spoon and the rest of the roux will be okay.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Mix the margarine, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Stir in flour and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.
Just before serving, put whipping cream on cookie.
Sprinkle with walnuts, M&M's, chocolate chips, candy bars, etc.
Refrigerate.

title: classic dressing
directions: Pour milk into a 4-cup glass measurer.
Blend in next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Beat smooth. Microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until thick, stirring after 30 seconds.
Stir a little warm mixture into egg yolk.
Then pour egg yolk into hot mixture.
Microwave on Medium 1 to 2 minutes until thick.
Stir in vinegar and oil.
Let cool.

title: taffy
directions: Stir all ingredients until mixed and then don't stir while cooking. Cook to hard ball stage (255° to 260°). Pour into three pans which have been buttered.
Cool until able to handle and pull.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all
together
and cook in greased bowl at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Alternate ingredients in baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: chipper chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crush potato chips.
Melt butter and add seasonings. Roll chicken in seasoned butter and then roll in the potato chips. Place prepared chicken on cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam). Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate bonbon candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with nuts, sugar, coconut and milk.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together.
Dip balls into chocolate mix.
Chill.

title: blonde cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix nuts, melted butter, cake mix and egg together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan, slightly greased.
Combine eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese well enough to spread over cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown. Cut into small squares.
Very rich and good!

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with sliced lemon or fish, oysters or clams.

title: diet lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add Italian seasoning, dry onion and tomato sauce.
Mix cottage cheese and egg.
Put spinach in a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 of meat mixture and 1/2 of cottage cheese and egg mixture.
Add 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Put beans over cheese and add rest of meat mixture, then rest of cottage cheese and egg.
Add 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: chili pork chops(microwave)
directions: Score fat on pork chops and place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish or 7 x 11-inch dish.
Place onion slice and bell pepper ring on each pork chop.
Pour whole bottle of chili sauce over pork chops. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on 70% power for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in milk, cranberries and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan.

title: traditional cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread into small pieces.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute celery and onion until tender.
In large bowl, combine bread, celery, onion, sage and pepper.
Stir in broth and eggs to cornbread mixture. Blend well.

title: strawberry fruit gel(96 calories per serving)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen berries; let thaw.
Add pineapple and bananas; chill.
Top with yogurt.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip boneless chicken in beaten egg in bowl and coat in 2nd bowl with bread crumbs.
Cook chicken in oil in large frypan, turning several times until lightly brown.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add chili or browned hamburger.
Add Ro-Tel and stir.
Makes great dip for tortilla chips.

title: sweet-sour pork chops
directions: Mix ginger, salt, pepper, paprika and flour together.
Coat both sides of chops in this mixture.
Melt shortening in skillet; add chops and cook over low heat until browned on both sides.
Pour in orange juice and vinegar; sprinkle with sugar. Cook over a low heat for 40 minutes or until chops are tender when tested with a fork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, place half of the asparagus in bottom of dish.
Layer half of chestnuts and half of crumbs.
Dot with half of butter.
Pour half of soup, thinned with liquid from asparagus. Repeat layers, ending with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black forest  cheese cake
directions: To Make Crust:
Mix flour, cocoa, 1/3 cup sugar and butter. Cut with pastry blender until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bourbon wienies
directions: Cut wienies in chunks and parboil. Simmer all seasonings until thickens slightly.
Add wienies and put in crock-pot on low.

title: cranberry roast pork
directions: Rub the roast with the salt and pepper and place on a rack in a baking dish.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put together dry ingredients; work in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add to buttermilk.
Pour liquid into dry mixture and stir until all flour is moistened. Cover and place in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut.
Place sides touching, on baking sheet.
Bake at 425°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
In medium pan, bring water, cocoa and margarine to boil.
Immediately add to dry ingredients; mix well and add eggs, sour cream and soda, mixing after each addition.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in greased sheet cake pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Prepare frosting while cake is baking.

title: krunch cake
directions: Mix all together in bowl, except nuts.
Beat 12 minutes; fold in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven.

title: saucepan chocolate cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and soda.
In large saucepan, combine margarine, water and cocoa; bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Using electric hand mixer, beat 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: easy gelatin parfait
directions: Mix gelatin according to package directions.
In separate bowl, mix part of the gelatin with Cool Whip.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling mixture in center of each won ton wrapper. Moisten the edges, bring the four corners to the center and press firmly to seal.
Place on baking sheet, then in freezer for 30 minutes.
Deep fry at 425° until golden brown.
(Peanut oil works best.)
Turn upside down and cool on paper towels.

title: cinnamon apple tea ring
directions: Divide dough in half.
Roll each into a 14 x 7-inch oblong. Brush with melted margarine.
Combine apples, sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of mixture over dough.
Roll up from long side.
Seal edges.
Place sealed edges down in circle on greased baking sheets.
Bring ends together and seal to form a ring.
Cut 2/3 into ring with scissors at 1-inch intervals.
Turn each section on its side.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine and stir well.
Chill until ready to use.

title: my favorite shoo-fly pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut together flour, brown sugar and margarine with pastry blender.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for topping. Combine in mixing bowl, syrup, egg, cold water, baking soda and hot water.
Add crumb mixture to liquid mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: sunday ham
directions: Place ham in roaster.
Combine mustard and sugar.
Spread over ham.
Place potatoes around ham. Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Cream in margarine and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add nuts if you want to.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish. Cover with crunch topping. Cook for 35 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine and water in a pan. Add the flour. Stir and remove from the heat. Add the eggs, one at a time. Spread on a cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove and cool.
Mix together the pudding and milk.
Whip the cream cheese. Combine the pudding and cream cheese.
Spread over cream puff. Top with the Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Simmer hash browns, onion, margarine and water. Add milk, corn and Cheddar cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cream.
Gradually add the cream while beating slowly and constantly until the mixture thickens to the desired consistency.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Makes holes in cake about 1 1/2 inches apart with fork.

title: turkey lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne and spread out side-by-side on a biscuit board. Blend next 9 ingredients in a large bowl and set aside.
In another bowl, blend cottage cheese, skim milk, mayonnaise, parsley and dressing; set aside.

title: cheese cake
directions: Use ingredients at room temperature.
Put cottage cheese through ricer into the large bowl of your mixer.
Add cream cheese and cream together at low speed for 10 minutes.
While mixer is turning, gradually add sugar, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch, sour cream and melted margarine; beat well for 5 minutes, scraping sides with a spatula.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Shut oven off; let cake cool in the oven for 2 hours.

title: cherry delight
directions: Butter a 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place the cherry pie filling in pan. Top with the cake mix.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Delicious warm or cold.
Does not need to be refrigerated if any is left.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onions.
In separate bowl, blend sugar, vinegar and mayo together and pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss to coat.
Chill 2 hours to overnight. Just before serving, sprinkle bacon and pecans over mixture and toss.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creole chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Saute in 3 tablespoons fat until brown.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Saute onion, pepper and garlic in remaining tablespoon of fat.
Add to chicken. Add tomatoes, celery and bay leaf to chicken mixture. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Add rice and mix well. Cover and simmer 5 more minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and put in an 11 x 16-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: all american apple pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except for apples. Add apples to mixture tossing to coat.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Roll pie crust pastry 1-inch larger than top of casserole.
Cut slits in pastry.
Place pastry over apple mixture. Seal and flute to rim of casserole.
Cover edge of pie with foil. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for an additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Crust should be golden and filling bubbly.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cold chicken salad torte(torta de bolacha com frango)
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to cover, using bouillon in water.
Boil until very tender.
Save the broth.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of crackers that have been well moistened in broth.
Cover with mayo and a layer of shredded chicken.
Continue process until chicken is gone, ending with mayonnaise on crackers. Allow to moisten in fridge several hours.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, paprika or parsley.

title: 7-up surprise punch
directions: Chill 7-Up and pineapple juice.
Pour additional 7-Up into ice trays.
Place cherry in each cube.
Freeze cubes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening. Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips. Roll into small balls.
Roll in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: judge roy bean's family's 100 year old pound cake
directions: Beat butter until very light and fluffy; a little at a time, add sugar, flour and eggs, one at a time, beating well after adding each.
After adding last egg, beat 5 minutes and then add flavorings.
The secret to a good pound cake is in the beating. Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Cook cranberries and water in a covered kettle until their skin pops.
Puree berries.
Add sugar, cloves and rinds.
Stir thoroughly.
Chill.
Add the lemon and apple juices.
Stir to blend.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with thin slices of orange. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: crunchy oven baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine oregano, paprika, basil, onion, garlic, pepper and bread crumbs.
In another bowl, place egg whites.
Dip chicken in egg white, then bread crumb mixture.
Spray shallow pan with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until chicken is brown.
Turn once.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Place boned chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Mix soup and water; pour over top.
Add sliced mushrooms over top. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt the bar in a double boiler.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup to mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: In ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix well with fork.
Make three holes in mixture with spoon.
Pour vinegar in first hole, vanilla in the second hole and oil in the third hole.
Pour water mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
(To double recipe, bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with Buddig ham, chopped fine.
Add Worcestershire, Accent, seasoned salt and onions.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: overnite lasagne
directions: Cook meat, drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine Ricotta or cottage cheese, oregano and egg; mix well.
Spread 1 1/2 cups of meat sauce in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 noodles, 1/2 Ricotta mixture and 1/2 Mozzarella.
Repeat with remaining noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Top with remaining meat sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add Parmesan last 5 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape meatballs.
Place in flat pan.

title: hungry jack biscuits barbecups
directions: Grease or line muffin pans.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: fresh pineapple dip
directions: Half the pineapple lengthwise.
Cut out pineapple meat.
Turn halves to drain.
Refrigerate.
Taste pineapple.
If it does not taste good, use canned pineapple.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and pineapple.
Refrigerate until serving.
Put dip in pineapple halves and surround with gingersnaps.
This is pretty and so good.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: monroeville country club bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and flour, mixed with cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread this very stiff batter with a spatula onto cookie sheet.
Glaze dough with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until vegetables and meat are done. Can be made in crock-pot and cooked 5 or 6 hours on slow.

title: banana muffins
directions: In a small bowl, sift together flour, nutmeg, salt and baking soda.
Add nuts and stir to coat.
In a medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and mashed banana to butter mixture and stir to blend.
Add flour mixture, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased
muffin tins two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 12 muffins.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Bring to a boil and stir until thick and clear.
Add Jell-O.
Cool slightly.
Place berries in shell.
Pour mixture over.
Chill thoroughly and serve with whipped cream.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool.
Invert on serving plate.
Prick top with fork.
Drizzle and smooth glaze evenly over top and sides.
Allow cake to absorb glaze.
Repeat until glaze is used up.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add lemonade concentrate (straight from can).
Mix slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into cooled baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.

title: dough boys
directions: Mix Bisquick with water to form a stiff dough.
Form on the blunt end of a green stick about as big as your thumb.
Hold over fire until browned and done.
Remove from stick and put jelly, sugar or butter in the hole.

title: pickled tomatoes
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add to tomatoes.
Bring to a hard boil only. Remove from heat and pour into hot jars.
Seal.

title: venison casserole
directions: Cut venison in 1-inch cubes or small pieces. Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve on rice, noodles or toast points.

title: beef and noodle soup
directions: Cook stew beef in crock-pot until tender (about 3 hours on high).
Then put in chopped carrots and chopped celery.
Cook for 30 more minutes.
Place noodles in and let simmer for about 1 hour on medium.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: festive herb dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill at least one hour. Makes 2 cups.
If desired can add either clams or Blue cheese.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; set in refrigerator until syrupy.
Put milk in a big bowl in freezer until icy.
Meanwhile, set cream cheese out to soften.
Take out milk and whip until like whipped cream; then gradually add sugar and then vanilla.
Stir in jello; beat cream cheese until soft.
Add to mixture.
Pour into a graham cracker crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine and press into a 9 x 12-inch greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix hamburger, cracker crumbs, water, salt and pepper.
Flatten out on cookie sheet.
Store in refrigerator (covered) 4 to 6 hours. Cut into squares, coated with flour and brown on each side.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole dish.
Mix gravy mix for gravy and add the mushroom soup.
After cooking, pour over meat and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin fritters
directions: In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, egg, flour, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in the raisins.
Form batter into 20 loosely packed 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat 1-inch of oil to 375°.
Drop fritters into the oil, being careful not to crowd and brown well on all sides.
Drain fritters on paper towels and sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil. Add peanuts. Stir constantly and cook until mixture turns light brown in color. (This is a very important part of making peanut brittle. You want to make sure it has a good color.) Remove mixture from heat. Add the baking soda and salt.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Spread in pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Now take rest of ingredients and beat and put on next layer.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Mix oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire, garlic, pepper and salt.
Add beef pieces.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn meat occasionally.
Thread meat onto skewers. Broil until meat is desired doneness.
Turn often.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until it is soft.
Mix all ingredients and sprinkle with paprika.
Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Cream sugars, shortening, vanilla, eggs and peanut butter. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, depending on size. Yields about 10 dozen.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef soup mix, egg, bread crumbs and milk.
In foil lined baking pan, shape beef mixture into an 8 x 5-inch loaf.
Bake in
a 350° oven 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
If desired, serve with tomato sauce.

title: broccoli-cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower, covered, in 1/2 chicken broth for 5 minutes, until tender.
In remaining broth, cook broccoli, mustard and dill, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; keep warm.
Place cauliflower and mace in blender; blend until smooth.
In large saucepan, cook onion in butter until almost tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cauliflower, broccoli and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or so.
Can be made ahead.
Serves 12.

title: pickled squash
directions: Use small squash, sliced thin.
Add sliced onion and peppers and mix.
Put layer of squash; sprinkle salt over this, then layer of ice.
Continue until all squash, peppers and onions are used up. Put ice on top.
Let stand about 3 or 4 hours.
Drain off water. Rinse in cool water and drain.
Mix together all other ingredients. Bring to boil.
Add squash and heat thoroughly.
Do not let the squash boil hard, it is better if squash does not boil but just simmers to heat it good.

title: oriental express
directions: In skillet, cook celery, green pepper and onions in butter until tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and brown sugar. Gradually blend into vegetable mixture.
Cook stirring until thickened.
Add chicken and pineapple, stir together.
Put bean sprouts on top cover, heat through on low heat.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Bring to boiling point and pour over pickles.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle in bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 14-inch pan (about 2-inches deep).
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour on top of coconut and nuts in pan.
Melt margarine in a small pan on low heat.
Add cream cheese.
When softened, add powdered sugar; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: chicken, broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, rice and chicken separately (as you would normally cook them).
I boil 6 boneless, skinless chicken breasts and then tear them into pieces.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, soup and Miracle Whip.
Put broccoli, rice, chicken and 1/2 the shredded cheese in a bowl.
Add 1/2 the soup mixture.
Put mixture in a glass casserole dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top and top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Microwave on High approximately 15 minutes with paper towel on top.

title: pork roast
directions: Mix ingredients together and place over roast.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
I leave uncovered until brown, then cover.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese in medium size bowl.
Drain olives, pimiento and chilies.
Add to cream cheese.
Add seasonings and lemon juice.
If too thick, add a little milk.
Spread the mix on the tortillas and roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill well. Then slice in 1/2-inch slices.
These freeze well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar lightly; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar or 1 cup powdered sugar. Spread on cooled crust. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until set.

title: fruit cocktail pie(no bake)
directions: Stir together.
Use a graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hoosier barbecue
directions: Cover any combination of meat with just enough water to cover and simmer 3 hours or until tender.
Shred immediately and reserve broth.
Add to shredded meat catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pickle relish and paprika.
Add reserved broth until desired consistency is reached.
This freezes well.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color. Add sugar; beat about 4 minutes. Add oil, vanilla and other ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: russian pastry
directions: Work butter into flour and salt.
Add egg yolks and sour cream and mix until well blended.
Divide dough into 6 sections, shape each into a ball and lightly coat with flour.
Refrigerate dough for several hours or overnight until well chilled.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Pour ketchup and Pepsi into a large pot.
Place washed chicken pieces in the mixture.
Bring to a boil and keep at a gentle rolling boil.
Mixture will gradually cook away and coat chicken. Cook about an hour.
Sauce is also good with pork chops.

title: light corn bread
directions: Mix all the given ingredients together well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Partially melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove and stir rapidly until melted.
Cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to shortening; mix well.
Blend in chocolate.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan while still hot and place under tightly fitting cover until cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and sour cream in small bowl and add to drained squash.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter and spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top of vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water.
Mix	together; flour, baking
powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk in
which soda has been dissolved.
Mix well, roll out on board. Cut
with
biscuit	cutter,
place on baking sheet, oil tops lightly,
store in refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Remove from refrigerator, let rise slightly, bake 15 minutes at 375°, until brown.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry pork until golden brown. Remove and set aside. Discard all but 2 tablespoons fat. Add onions to fat and saute until soft. Add potatoes and boiling water. Bring to boil and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, 12 to 15 minutes. Add fish and continue cooking for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Add the milk and half and half; season with salt and pepper. Heat (do not boil). Garnish each serving with some of reserved pork and crumbled crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix peanut butter, sugar and eggs. Roll the mixture into 1-inch balls with floured hands.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until 1 cookie appears dry on top.
After cooling for a minute or two on the cookie sheet, press Hershey Kisses into each cookie.
Transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

title: garden marinara sauce
directions: Dip fresh tomatoes in boiling water to cover for 10 seconds. Core and peel.
Chop fresh or canned tomatoes with food processor or knife.
Pour oil into a 12 to 14-inch frying pan.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until onions are golden brown (about 20 minutes).
Add chopped tomatoes and basil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking until sauce in reduced to 8 cups (45 to 60 minutes).
Add sugar; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle sauce into four 1-pint canning jars or freezer containers, leaving 1 inch headspace.
Cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator for up to 1 week or in freezer for up to 6 months.
Makes 6 pints.

title: apple bake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine together to form crumbly mixture.
Set aside.
Peel and slice apples in 8 x 8-inch pan. Cover with cinnamon and then water.
Put sugar, flour and margarine mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture is browned.

title: lipton onion roast
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Slice carrots.
Place meat, potatoes and carrots on heavy-duty foil in a shallow pan.
Top with sliced mushrooms, then sprinkle everything with Lipton soup mix.
Seal the foil tightly.
Roast for 1 to 2 hours at 375°.

title: pumpkin streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon (reserve).
Beat cake mix (dry), water, eggs, pumpkin and baking soda in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Spread half of the batter in pan; sprinkle with half of the reserved brown sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining batter and brown sugar mixture. Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center or when wooden pick inserted in center comes out clear.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yummy icing
directions: Melt sugar, milk and marshmallows, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips and margarine.
Mix well.
Ice the warm cake. Yields icing for 1 large cake or 2 sheet cakes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger.
Chop and mix in onions, peppers and corn. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice cheese and cover mixture.
Mix cornbread mix and pour over mixture and cheese.
Bake in oven at 425° for 25 minutes (until cornbread has browned).

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onions; add chili powder and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese. (Save the other half of the cheese for the top of casserole.) Add beaten egg and tomato sauce. Take pan off of heat and add sour cream. Mix thoroughly.

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray pan or line with foil.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted margarine, then in cheese bread crumbs, etc. mixture.
Place in pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and grate.
Add salt and pepper.
Lightly toss potatoes, sour cream, Cheddar cheese (save a little for the top) and the onions.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Put dobs of butter on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frances chocolate logs
directions: Mix ingredients well. Form small logs. Place on wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour. While logs are cooling, put 1 bag semi-sweet chocolate morsels and 1/2 block paraffin wax in as double boiler (water in bottom boiler). If mixture is too thick, you may need to add a little more wax. When completely melted, dip logs in mixture, then place on wax paper. Better if kept in a cool place. Yields 50.

title: eagle brand cheese pie
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks until golden in color; add lemon juice and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into crust and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: msgr. charles bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add nuts, 1 cup flour, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well. Remove 1 cup of mixture and refrigerate.
To remainder of mixture, add eggs.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to egg mixture.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with reserved 1 cup spice mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool before cutting into squares.
Bread will keep 1 week or can be frozen.
Serve with tea in late afternoon.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix water and butter in a saucepan; bring to rolling boil.
Add almond extract and remove from heat.
Add flour and stir until thick and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each egg.
Divide and spread on first layer.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until brown and crisp at 350°.

title: chuck wagon baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and set aside to cool.
In same pan cook hamburg, onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Dissolve the bouillon in 2/3 cup of boiling water.
Mix in large bowl, the beans, mustard, ketchup, garlic powder, pepper.
Add hamburg mix and bouillon.
Stir together.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Crumble bacon and stir into mixture.
Place in large covered baking dish. Bake at 350° 1 1/2 hours.

title: rusty's coffee cake
directions: Cream together the cup of Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat eggs and combine with sour cream and vanilla.
Add to the creamed Crisco and sugar combination.
Gradually mix in flour.

title: low-fat snickers pie
directions: Soften and mix all ingredients.
Top with a small layer of additional Cool Whip.
Refreeze in an 8-inch square pan.
Cut into 8 equal servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Punch holes all over the cake with a fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over cake. Put the drained pineapple on the cake, then the Cool Whip.
Keep the cake in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: delicious chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling salted water until tender. (This can be cooked with no salt.)
Put pieces onto bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix together soups and water in a separate bowl. Add broccoli to soup mixture.
Spoon over chicken, then spread stuffing mix with the spices included. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and drain.
Cover beans with 4 to 5 cups water, salt, chicken broth, bay leaf, black pepper and garlic powder. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 1 1/2 hour. At this time, add greens with liquid, carrots, potatoes and onion. Cook, covered, until beans and vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.
Do not eat bay leaf.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg.
Mix flour and dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture; alternate with soda, dissolved in milk.
Add vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.

title: seashell macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all ingredients except soup, cheese and
macaroni.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add soup and cooked
macaroni;
mix
well.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven to melt cheese.

title: homemade ice cream sodas
directions: In tall glass put milk, chocolate syrup and vanilla ice cream. Almost fill with chilled plain soda water.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: hot spicy apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.

title: carolina corn pudding
directions: Stir all together the corn, salt, sugar and butter.
Mix together eggs and milk; stir into corn mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: southwestern steak
directions: Combine lime juice, steak sauce, salsa, oil, garlic and pepper in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place steak in marinade and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally. Grill steak on medium coals 12 to 14 minutes or broil in oven.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until blended.
Add egg and beat.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add to cream mixture at low speed until just blended.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together; add to the cereal; coat them.
Pour into 2 cups powdered sugar that's in a paper bag. Shake well.
Store in an airtight container.

title: white chili
directions: Place beans in heavy pot. Add cold water to cover 3 inches. Soak overnight. Cook chicken in large saucepan. Add cold water to cover and simmer until tender. Drain chicken, cool, remove skin, cut into cubes. Drain beans. Heat oil in bean pot. Add onions and saute until clear. Stir in garlic, chilies, and spices. Saute 2 minutes. Add beans and stock (or broth) and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours until beans are tender. Add chicken and cheese. Heat through.

title: cherry or apple dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple (juice included) into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pie filling over this.
Add coconut and pecans, then sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet blueberry muffins
directions: *If frozen, don't thaw.

title: witches' brew
directions: Mix punch, 7-Up and ice cream (in scoops).
Add dry ice just before serving (it will bubble and smoke).
Serve in punch cups.

title: chilled strawberry soup in melon bowls
directions: This lo-cal soup served for breakfast or first course for a warm weather dinner. Makes 4 servings.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Combine all ingredients together; salt and pepper.
Chill before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: oysters in a blanket
directions: Pick over the oysters carefully. Pat dry and roll in a slice of bacon. Fasten with a small skewer. Cook in a hot chafing dish until bacon is crisp. Season and serve very hot. Serves 2.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 2 tsp. per cup of hot water.

title: microwave brown sugar beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Mix well. Cover and cook on High 4 minutes or until heated.
Stir every minute. Serves 4.

title: chicken breasts ala valdostana
directions: Flour chicken and saute in butter very quickly on medium heat. Saute on both sides.
Add wine and flour to thicken.
When chicken looks almost done, place cheese slices on top.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry chills
directions: Roll out pie crusts and place in jelly roll pan.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes and cool.
Whip cream cheese and powdered sugar. Whip whipping cream separately.
Fold cream cheese mixture and whipping cream together.
Spread on pie crust and chill.
Just before serving, spread blueberry pie filling on top.
Slice and serve.

title: aunt sissy's carrot cake
directions: Mix well oil, sugar and eggs.
Combine and sift all dry ingredients and add to first mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and carrots.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. (Makes 3 layers.)
Bake 25-28 minutes in preheated 350 degree oven.

title: little rich cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form small balls of dough on cookie sheet, flatten out.
Bake
in
oven
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat in flour.
Add flavoring and pecans.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove immediately.

title: coffee cake
directions: Boil 2 cups strong coffee with 1 box raisins until coffee is gone.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and spices three times.
Add to creamed mixture and then add raisins and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Cook 2 hours at 250°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables (celery, carrots, cauliflower, cucumbers, green peppers, etc.).

title: neighbors coffee cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Coat a 9x13 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, cream together 1 c. butter and 1 1/2 c. sugar.	Add eggs one at a time.
Add 3 c. flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread half the batter in a baking dish.
Using a wet knife, spread the pie filling evenly over the batter.
Then dollop the remaining batter over the pie filling.
In a small bowl mix with fork the remaining, 1/4 c. flour, 1/4 c. sugar, 2 tsp. butter and cinnamon until crumbly. Sprinkle over batter and bake 50-60 minutes or wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 12-15.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, sugar and oil.
Then add eggs vanilla and almond.
Add one cup at a time of mixed dry ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: rhoda's brownie dessert
directions: Make brownies according to pkg. directions 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake only 20 minutes.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Put shredded zucchini in saucepan with water.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Add sugar and crushed pineapple.
Cook an additional 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add apricot jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars.
This marmalade must be refrigerated.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and pour over oatmeal; mix.
Add other ingredients. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
While cake is hot, spread on the topping and put under broiler; cook until topping is bubbly and hot, only a minute or two, depending on your oven.

title: butterscotch or chocolate morsels
directions: Whip the cream until very stiff.
Fold in the chocolate ice cream topping or syrup and creme de cacao thoroughly.
Turn into individual souffle cups or line muffin tins with paper cupcake liners and fill with mixture.
Cover.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 4 hours.
Serve frozen, topped with chocolate shaving for garnish if desired.

title: unleavened brownies
directions: In a two-quart saucepan over low heat, melt and blend chocolate and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, heating well after each addition.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: banana chip muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg, oil and sugar until smooth.
Stir in bananas.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into the banana mixture just until moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill greased muffin cups three-fourths full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Makes 18 (medium-size) muffins.

title: quickie chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Noodles Romanoff according to package directions except use 3/4 cup milk.
Add soup, chicken, broccoli and olives.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Place chicken and vegetables in marinade for 3 to 4 hours.
I prefer to parboil onions before placing them in the marinade. Skewer separately to adjust for different cooking times.
Broil on grill, basting frequently.
Serve with rice in center of hot platter with the grilled food circling it.

title: baked pretzel snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break pretzels into bite size pieces. Mix oil and spices and pour over the pretzels.
Mix well to coat all pretzels.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave velveeta salsa dip
directions: Preparation Time: 5 minutes.
Cooking Time: 5 minutes. Microwave Cooking Time: 5 minutes.

title: spinach and cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the eggs in a bowl.
Sift dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Add milk, cheese and well drained spinach; mix well.
Spread in pan on top of melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Put potatoes and onions in large bowl.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove to paper towel.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add bell pepper and cook over medium heat about 2 minutes.
Add to potatoes.
Pour vinegar into skillet and add salt and pepper and cook over medium heat until hot.
Pour over potatoes and crumble bacon over top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle chopped nuts on wax paper and put mixture on nuts, forming a ball.

title: peck's fruit salad
directions: Cut apples and place in lemon juice.
Slice bananas and pour lemon juice over them.
Drain when ready to add to other fruit. Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch dish. Mix next 3 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix your oil and egg together, then add this to the flour mixture.
Sprinkle this over apple mixture.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In each of six muffin cups, place 1 teaspoon of margarine and 1 teaspoon of brown sugar.
Place in oven to melt.
Mix remaining ingredients, except pecan halves. Beat vigorously for 1/2 minute.
Remove muffin cups from oven. Place three pecan halves on each butter-sugar mixture in the muffin cups.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups (batter will be thick).
Bake for 15 minutes.
Immediately invert pan after removing from oven to prevent sticking.
Makes 6.

title: chocolate-peppermint sauce
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, 1/2 cup half and half and candy in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until candy melts.
Stir in enough remaining half and half for desired consistency.
Serve warm over waffles, pound cake or ice cream.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar and dates together in saucepan.
Cook slowly; stir occasionally.
When mixture leaves the pan something like scrambled eggs, remove from heat.
Add the Rice Krispies and nuts.
Stir well and drop or shape into balls.
Roll in shredded coconut.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine wheat bran cereal, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, raisins, walnuts and salt.
Combine buttermilk, egg, molasses and oleo in another bowl.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients quickly with only a few strokes. Do not overmix.
Place paper liners in a muffin tin and divide batter equally.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Freezes well for microwaving to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and sprinkle on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Puncture oranges with 10 cloves each.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Let stand overnight.
Add 1/2 bottle rum, if desired, for alcoholic punch.

title: whole wheat zucchini bread
directions: Beat together for 1 minute:
white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini.
Sift in and stir to moisten white flour, whole wheat flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Can add couple of oranges and water.
Bake at 350° in two greased loaf pans, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl combine broccoli (finely chopped), 1/2 cup raisins, small onion (finely chopped) and bacon strips (chopped). Then mix dressing in another bowl (mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar). Add to broccoli.
Let chill and serve.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix beef, onion, egg, bread, salt and pepper; make 16 meatballs.
Brown in skillet; pour off fat.
Blend in soup, sour cream and water.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir now and then. Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Blend well.
Add raisins, walnuts, applesauce and soda.
Fold in flour in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a floured and greased pan 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato biscuits(from blue pete's restaurant in virginia beach)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Boil, steam or microwave sweet potatoes, then mash or process in the food processor.
While still hot, measure 1 1/2 cups into a bowl with butter, sugar, salt and milk and mix well.
Sift together the flour and baking powder at least twice to thoroughly combine.
Add flour to the mixture using your hands to made soft dough.
Roll out and cut square biscuits.
Bake on top shelf in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Thoroughly mix all of ingredients and pour into sifted flour. Knead until very stiff.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutter and bake at low temperature, 300° or 325°.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil boneless breasts for 1 hour.
Cut and spread chicken in rectangular dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and place over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with stick of butter.
Pour over top along with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all except the pecans.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: summertime punch
directions: Early in day or day ahead:
In medium bowl, mix 3 cups cran-raspberry drink and 2 cups water; pour 3 1/2 cups of this drink mix into a 6-cup ring mold; freeze.
Refrigerate remainder.

title: honey's chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into pieces and mix with all other ingredients, except crescent rolls.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Roll crescent rolls into one large piece and place over chicken mixture.
Brush top with margarine and sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caribbean chicken drums($25,000 winner)
directions: In frypan, place oil and heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken; cook, turning, about 10 minutes, or until brown on all sides.
Add tomatoes, chilies, brown sugar and allspice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low temperature and cook 20 minutes.
Add mango chutney, lemon juice and raisins.
Cover; cook about 15 minutes, or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Remove chicken to serving platter.

title: cinnamon quickies
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Flatten bread with a rolling pin. Spread each piece with a light layer of cream cheese.
Roll slices of bread tightly.
Cut rolls into quarters.
Prepare a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Dip each roll into melted butter, then roll in the cinnamon and sugar mix.
Place rolls on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When rolls are frozen, store in plastic baggies.
When ready to serve, place rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until rolls are bubbly and puffy.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add water, marinara sauce and salt; bring to a boil.
In 2-quart (11 x 7-inch) baking dish, layer hot sauce, uncooked noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tightly covered casserole dish at 275° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix butter, oil and marshmallows.
Pour over rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Press in buttered tube pan and cover for awhile before removing from pan.

title: no-fat chocolate-cherry cake
directions: Beat cake mix with pie filling, eggs, water and cocoa powder with mixer on slow speed until well combined. Then increase speed and beat 2 to 3 minutes more. Divide batter into 2 layer pans (sprayed with cooking spray) or put in 1 (14 x 10) glass pan, sprayed, and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely and ice with Cool Whip. May garnish with maraschino cherries for added color and taste.

title: picadillo(savory ground beef)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute the onions and green pepper until the onion is translucent, about 3 minutes.
Add the garlic and cook 2 minutes more.

title: grandma stacey's pumpkin pie
directions: In bowl mix pumpkin with half milk and half water (put 1 cup milk in pumpkin can and add water to fill can).
Add eggs, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken rice casserole
directions: Prepare wild rice according to package directions.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but do not brown.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cook 1 box raisins until plump.
Save 1 cup juice.
Let cool. Mix together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Then add flour, raisins, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix all together. Drop by teaspoonful on greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a hard boil. Add the cukes and the onions.
Let mixture boil until the cukes change color. Put in jars and seal.

title: spiced pita bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Split pita breads in half and brush with mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and broil 4 - 5 inches from heat until golden brown.

title: mushroom onion rice
directions: Combine rice, onion soup mix, consomme, water, mushrooms, parsley, margarine and onions in 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Combine above and put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle corn chips over top.
Preheat oven and bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until just heated through.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix the squash, sour cream, onion, carrots and soup together. Crumble the stuffing mix and mix with the butter.
Put half of the stuffing mixture on the bottom of a baking dish; add the squash mixture and top with the rest of the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Form the dough into long logs in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: never fail fudge icing
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let come to a good rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool a few minutes in cold water, then beat well and spread on cake.
Will ice two 9-inch layers.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (butter, cocoa, sugar and milk). Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in oats and vanilla. Drop on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Combine other ingredients and bake until done.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, 2 at a time and add vanilla and cake flour.
Mix well and pour into greased and lightly floured tube pan with wax paper in bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: arkansas cheese
directions: Heat cream cheese, tomato sauce and lemon Jell-O until melted. Pour over the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Let chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage, cheese, grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart baking dish.

title: candy
directions: Pour milk into skillet; add cocoa and mix together.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thickened (like gravy), add 1/2 cup nuts.
Allow to cool until able to handle. Roll into small balls and roll each in coconut.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Served daily in U. S. Senate dining room.
Wash beans and soak overnight in large kettle.
The next morning, add enough water to make 5 quarts.
Add ham bone or hock and simmer about 2 hours or until beans begin to be mushy.
Add potatoes, onions, celery and garlic.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bone, dice meat and return it to soup.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: dutch carrots
directions: Slice all vegetables; cook carrots until slightly undercooked. Drain.
While carrots are still hot, add all the rest of ingredients.
Mix and cover.
Put in refrigerator for at least overnight or more for best flavor.

title: coconut brunch bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salad oil.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Generously grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan (or use smaller pans).
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Arrange bite size pieces of sausage in bottom of pie crust. Add cheese.
Pour rest of combined ingredients on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Test with knife.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, milk and cheese soup; add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour over veggies.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° or less until brown.

title: clam pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Arrange cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Romano cheeses on top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 15 minutes in tiny, lightly greased muffin tins.
Makes 24 tiny rolls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until thick.

title: orange slice dessert
directions: Mix fruit with cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello over fruit and cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Fold in bowl of Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Break up bananas.
Add other ingredients.
Beat until all mixed.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until brown.

title: slow cooker casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce to low and cook 4 to 8 hours.

title: beer buns
directions: Mix all together.
Will be lumpy.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mama pearl's corn relish
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Cook 30 minutes.
Put in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: orange, sweet potato and chop casserole
directions: Place potato slices in greased oblong baking dish.
Cover with orange slices.
Top with pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: tim downs' barbecue
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic and green pepper.
Drain fat. Add celery, bay leaf, tomatoes and catsup.
Add some water, if necessary.
Add spices and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything but paprika.
Place in casserole and top with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, both sugars and eggs. Beat well.
Add vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Roll in a small ball.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple puddingbolivar, missouri
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix eggs well and add to chopped apples and shortening and sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients and combine with other ingredients.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven until bacon looks done.
Stir occasionally and add more water if needed.
Should bake at least 1 hour.

title: ooma's brown rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion.
Add other ingredients and bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: trifle
directions: With pudding, add 2 cups of milk with 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice in pan.
Stir; let it come to a full boil.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut pound cake into cubes.
Cut fruit into little chunks. Put jam in pan.
Keep stirring.
When pudding cools, mix in 3/4 container of Cool Whip, then layer as follows:
pudding, cake, pineapple, 1/2 of the jam and 1/2 of other fruit.
Repeat.
Cover top with rest of Cool Whip.
Decorate top accordingly.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham, rolls and cheese.
Split whole pan of rolls in half and spread both sides with mixture on bottom half.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese and layer ham.
Put top of roll over ham and cheese.
Cut rolls and put back into baking tin.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: grandma goose's cranberry muffins
directions: Put the Cranberries in a plastic bag and mash lightly with a mallet or block.
Put mashed Berries in a big bowl and add Sugar and mix.
Mix ingredients well.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Pour in the batter.
Bake at 400 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; beat.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour and beat.
Add flavoring, 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; beat.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature at 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: remedy for whooping cough
directions: Simmer 4 hours.
Do
not boil.	Strain and add water to make 1 pint.
Add 2 ounces honey.	Take 1 tablespoon 4 times a day.

title: tuna melts(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on bagel halves.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the first 4 ingredients and stir by hand until well mixed.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mammaw's iced tea
directions: Boil first quart of water in an enamel pan or glass teapot. (Do not use metal, it flavors the tea.) Remove water from heat and add tea bags. Allow tea to steep for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove tea bags and pour into glass 2-quart pitcher.
Ad sugar while tea is still hot. Stir. Add second quart of water. Stir. Serve hot or on ice, with or without lemon.

title: dressing for cucumbers
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over four cups of cucumbers and onions.

title: strawberry compote with kirsch
directions: Combine sugar, water, vanilla and juice; boil.
Hull and wash strawberries.
When sugar mixture is thick, add strawberries and remove from heat.
Add Kirsch and cover 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake well and refrigerate.

title: can't fail five minute fudge
directions: Bring to boil the milk, sugar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chips, marshmallows and vanilla.
Mix until ingredients melt and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine ingredients in stainless steel or glass bowl.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in chilled cups.
Top with croutons, if desired.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla; let cool for 5 minutes. Beat until fudge starts to get stiff. Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan. Let set until hard.

title: nutty coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix together
pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Combine margarine, sugar, eggs,
sour
cream
and vanilla.
Sift together and into liquid mixture,
flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Pour 1/2 batter into
pan
and cover with most of nut mixture.
Add rest of batter and top with nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: celery and water chestnut casserole
directions: Parboil celery. Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces. Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Drain.
Mix with cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts.
Pour into casserole dish. Set aside. Crush the Ritz crackers. Add melted margarine.
Mix together and sprinkle over celery mixture. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix together crushed cookies and oleo.
Press half mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bananas on top of cookie mixture.
Melt over low heat the marshmallows and milk.
Mix together the Cool Whip and dry Dream Whip.
Add marshmallow mixture to Cool Whip mixture and spread over bananas.
Top with remaining Oreo mixture. Refrigerate overnight (at least 4 hours).
Serve.

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add onion and saute until soft. Add cabbage and saute until crisp and tender.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Stir noodles into cabbage mixture.
Add sour cream, if desired.
Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: punch recipe
directions: Mix together.
Can be chilled ahead of time. Pour over ice in punch bowl.
This is not a real sweet punch.
Good to serve with cakes, etc.
Also good for individuals watching their diets. Yields 24 (4 ounce) glasses.

title: two-corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In small skillet, melt margarine.
Add pepper and onion.
Saute until crisp and tender.
In a large bowl, blend corn, eggs and cornbread mix.
Blend well.
Add onion and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until firm or set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Mix onion, mayonnaise, sugar and red wine vinegar.
Add bacon and broccoli. Stir, then add sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Stir again and serve. Serves 4 to 6.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container. Dissolve 2 rounded teaspoonfuls in cup of hot water.
(Tastes great and really warms you up.)

title: tanya's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Prepare cornbread mix as directions on package.
Pour cornbread batter into a well buttered pan.
Mix meat, onion, Ranch Style beans, tomatoes and creamed corn together.
Pour over cornbread batter. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cornbread is brown.

title: shrimp de jongh
directions: Add to melted butter the garlic, parsley, paprika, pepper and cooking sherry.
Add bread crumbs.
Place shrimp in 11 x 17 1/2-inch dish.
Spoon butter mixture over top.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add small amount of milk and stir in eggs.
Add remaining milk slowly until smooth.
Add melted oleo and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: szechuan shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in 1 tablespoon sesame oil, garlic and onion. Remove.
Add the other tablespoon of oil, mushrooms, broccoli, pea pods, carrots, teriyaki and Szechuan.
Cook until crisp (5 minutes).
Add shrimp, garlic and onion back in.
Add water chestnuts and bean sprouts, if desired.
Add 1/4 cup orange juice. Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: poverty soup
directions: Cook beans in water with salt until done.
(Beans should be soaked for several hours to hasten cooking process.) Add remaining ingredients and cook about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box. Add instant vanilla pudding and condensed milk to the batter.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan. Pour chocolate chips into batter once the mixture is in the pan. Bake at 350° for 38 to 45 minutes.
A powdered sugar and milk glaze is a great topping, or it is wonderful by itself.

title: cheese bar
directions: Mix together and pour on top of 1st mixture. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl, mixing until smooth. Chill 15 minutes before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; let cool.
In large bowl add remaining ingredients to sugar/water mixture.
Mix and freeze. Use when desired.

title: syrian beef
directions: Brown stew beef.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and 4 tablespoons brown sugar.
When brown, add tomatoes, green beans, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Cook for 1 hour. Add cornstarch to cold water to thicken.
When done, serve over rice or noodles.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn, dry mustard and turmeric.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add corn, dry mustard and turmeric.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in clean jars; seal.
Process in hot water bath 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together
ground
beef,
rice, egg, onion, half cup tomato sauce,
catsup,
Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Arrange green pepper halves in
an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Fill
peppers
with	meat mixture.
Mix together remaining tomato
sauce,
water
and	sugar.	Pour
over green peppers. Cover with tight fitting plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 20
to
minutes
or until meat is no longer pink and green
pepper
is	tender.
Allow	to stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix condensed milk and ReaLemon.
Stir in pie filling and fruit cocktail; pour over crust.
Top with whipped topping and crumbs. Freeze 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before cutting.

title: pat's nacho chili dip
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch ovenproof pan, place cream cheese on bottom layer, chili mixed with desired amount of jalapenos and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.
Can be reheated if necessary.

title: angel delight pie
directions: Recipes Continued:
Recipes continue from page to page.
The computer controls the layout of the recipes as well as the hyphenations.
Never use the words ABOVE and BELOW.
If copy says "combine above ingredients" you must type "combine all ingredients."

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan and pat down.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cut into squares before chocolate is set. Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Saute
celery
and onion in oleo.
Mix all and	put
in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Lay chicken in greased pan; cover with Swiss cheese. Mix soup and wine together and pour over cheese. Sprinkle stuffing mix over top and dribble with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes.

title: chicken wings with honey and orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, prepare chicken wings and sauce.
Bake, uncovered, basting occasionally, for 40 minutes, or until chicken is done and sauce is thickened.

title: german chocolate ice cream cake
directions: Crush wafers and mix with butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Save about 1/2 cup for top.
Melt chocolate, sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Cool.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Spread over crumb crust.
Slice ice cream and fit into pan.
Cover chocolate completely, then cover top with crumbs.
Freeze for at least 4 hours.
Cover with foil.
Will keep several days.

title: pepperoni twist
directions: Brown hamburger and pepperoni.
Mix hamburger, pepperoni and both sauces together.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In meantime, cook macaroni as directed on package.
Pour macaroni in baking dish and pour sauce mixture over it and mix (do not stir, just pull macaroni to the sides and let the sauce fall down).
Put Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: mexican beef stew
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add soup broth, water, potatoes and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add corn and heat until hot.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Good with tortilla chips and sour cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare sliced peaches. Mix well with 1 cup sugar; set aside. Preheat oven 350°. Place margarine in deep baking dish and melt in oven. Stir batter of sugar, flour and milk. Pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Pour sugar peaches on top. Do not stir. Bake in oven for 1 hour. Batter will be brown and crisp.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Finely chop 1 1/2 packages of dried beef, reserving 4 or 5 pieces to wrap around cheese ball. Mix all ingredients together except 4 or 5 pieces of beef.
Wrap 4 or 5 pieces of dried beef around cheese ball.
Let stand for 4 hours or overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add melted butter and stir in eggs and vanilla.
Stir only enough to blend ingredients well.
(Do not use mixer.)
Add nuts, if desired, and bake in well-greased and floured, glass baking dish at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Beat well sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Simmer cranberries in water for 10 minutes. Add sugar, Jell-O, gelatine and pineapple.
Chill until partly set.
Add nuts and apples. Stir. Chill until firm.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Cut up or mince seasonings and add to chicken.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in an iron pot.
Add meat and seasonings together with gravy browning.
Cook for ten minutes, gradually adding boiling water to prevent sticking.
When seasoning is cooked, add curry and 3 cups of boiling water.
Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add Angostura aromatic Bitters 3 minutes before pot is taken off the stove.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat and onion well (drain).
Add water, green onions, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Bring to hard boil.
Add rice and bring to hard boil again.
Reduce heat and cook on low until rice is done, stirring occasionally.
Keep tightly covered when not stirring.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease casserole dish with oleo.
Put in desired amount of apples.
Mix the above ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toasted lemon meringue cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package. Cool. Split cake to make 3 layers.
Reserve a small amount of filling for decorating top. Fill layers with remaining filling.

title: carol cake
directions: Mix and add 1 cup boiling water or coffee.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 X 13 pan.
Or makes 36 cupcakes.

title: juicy hamburgers *
directions: Put into a 2-quart bowl and mix well.
Wet hand and shape into patties of desired size.
Brown in skillet over medium heat.
Turn once.
Do not flatten (this presses out the juices).
Serve on toasted split buns and with onions, relish and sauces desired.

title: divinity pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt together in heavy saucepan.
Add pumpkin and milk; stir to blend well.
Set over moderate heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thick and boiling.
Beat egg yolks; add about half of the hot mixture gradually to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to pan and bring back to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
