Add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture is blended.
Cool, do not chill.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Remove and brown ground beef.
Mix soup and soy sauce.
Mix all together and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sauteed apple wedges
directions: Melt butter in a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add apple and cook about 5 minutes, stirring 3 to 4 times, until almost tender.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cook 1 to 2 minutes more, until apples are tender and glazed.

title: barbara alpeter's maravian sugar cake
directions: Beat
with a mixer the white sugar, 3/4 cup melted oleo and hot mashed potatoes.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and let stand
minutes.
Add
well beaten eggs to 1st mixture. Add yeast
mixture.
Add
3 cups of flour and beat with mixer. Add 2 cups flour and beat with wooden spoon.
Cover; let rise until double.

title: coconut shortbread
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and shortening.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Cook 2-inches apart.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Wash and peel shrimp.
Butterfly by cutting 1/2 to 3/4 way through.
Put shrimp in casserole dish.
Dot each shrimp with butter.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and spices. Broil about 4-inches from broiler for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with rice and juices from shrimp.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and set aside.
In skillet, melt butter. Add onion and cook until done.
Set aside.
Add hamburger to pan and cook until well browned.
Mix in onion.
Put 1/2 of the macaroni in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Add meat, onion, corn, peas, tomatoes and celery.
Sprinkle red pepper, oregano and olives.
Pour half and half over top.
Add rest of macaroni and cheese and bake for 35 minutes at 375° or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound veal between 2 pieces of wax paper until paper thin. Dredge in flour and spices.
Saute mushrooms in 1/2 of butter, remove to warm plate.
Saute veal, adding remaining butter for 1 1/2 minutes each side.
Remove to plate of mushrooms.

title: spaghetti chop chop
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir ground beef until light brown.
Drain.
Slice 3 rings from green pepper.
Reserve for garnish.
Chop remaining green pepper.
Stir pepper and remaining ingredients, except cheese, into meat.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Top with green pepper rings; bake 5 minutes more.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and pour 1/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons lemon juice over hot bread.
Cool 10 minutes, then place on a rack.
Do not cut for 24 hours.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: You will need a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil in water for 20 minutes after adding 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drain when cooked.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard and salt.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together.
Add to first mixture.
Chill 20 minutes, then roll out. Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer (have Mom or Dad help), beat butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until well mixed.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Combine cinnamon and remaining 2 tablespoons sugar.
Roll balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 400° oven 6 to 8 minutes or until set.
Remove from baking sheets.
Let cool on wire racks.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients dry and store in airtight container.
Mix to taste in 1 cup of hot water.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You can also add 1/2 cup of peanuts to this.

title: hot tea
directions: Mix and store in tight container.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Bring sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar and water to a boil at 240°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour and separate on aluminum foil.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Shred cabbage and put in fish.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer them over the cabbage.
Spread onion over top of potatoes.
Crumble corned beef over onion layer, then pour soup over all.
Salt and pepper; cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot balls(makes 8 dozen)
directions: Put apricots through food grinder or grind about 4 ounces at a time in electric blender.
Combine ground apricots, milk, coconut and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Dampen hands with cold water and then form apricot mixture into 1/2 inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Chill before serving.

title: baked bananas
directions: With a knife, cut bananas lengthwise into halves.
Place in an ungreased baking dish.
Mix lemon juice and honey; spread on bananas.
Bake at 350° for approximately 5 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle more corn flakes on top.
Pour an additional 1/4 cup butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate filled snowballs
directions: Mix first five ingredients into a dough.
Use about 1 tablespoon of dough to shape around candy kisses and roll into a ball.
Make sure kiss is completely covered.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: ham ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Stir together all other ingredients.
Mold into ham ball.

title: slow cooked honey-dijon pork roast
directions: In 4 to 6-quart slow cooker, combine onion and apples.

title: grilled marinated chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring until well blended. Pour over chicken in a shallow container.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill over hot coals 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Turn and baste every 10 minutes with marinade. Serving amount is 1 breast half at 97 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
2 lean meat.

title: sausage balls or thins
directions: Crumble and fry sausage; drain.
Mix all together.
Make small balls in palm of hand.
You can leave them as balls or flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Yields 20 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together well and chill. Serve with pineapple, apples, strawberries, cantaloupe, green grapes and kiwi.

title: sausage balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix the ingredients and form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with cocktail picks.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: When pudding is cool, add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: parfait pie
directions: Dissolve jello in the hot water. Add fruit. Add ice cream. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until set. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in container and freeze.
Remove from freezer a little before serving.

title: bran bread
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and beat.
Add corn syrup and mix well. Add buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Add all-bran and raisins.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 5 tin cans.
Fill them about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 5 loaves, 10 slices a loaf.
Approximate calories per slice:

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken; pull apart. Add chopped onions, pecans and relishes; mix well. Stir in mayonnaise to desired consistency. Serve with crackers or bread.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef (and drain), bacon and onion.
Add and mix kidney beans, pork and beans, and butter beans.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add onion and saute with meat for 5 additional minutes. Add all other ingredients. Simmer and cover for 30 minutes.

title: butternut cake(very good)
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to directions on the box.
Add 1 tablespoon butternut flavoring.

title: beer cheese in pumpernickel shell
directions: In a blender, mix cheese, butter, sauce and beer. Make the day before for a thicker dip. Refrigerate if made ahead. Serve dip warm or cold. Hollow out the center of 1 of the loaves of bread to form a bowl. Cut the other loaf into bite size pieces for dipping. Arrange around the hollowed out loaf. Fill bowl with cheese.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies(7 dozen cookies)
directions: Melt butter; beat together with the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, bran and oats.
Stir mixture into butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Remove to a rack to cool.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir soup into mayonnaise.
Add to chicken.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole or a long casserole.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until bubbly, uncovered.

title: potato dish
directions: Place frozen hash browns in 9 x 13 dish. Mix 1/2 cup butter, soup, cheese and sour cream; place over hash browns. Crush corn flakes. Pour over top. Pour 1/2 cup butter over cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage leaves in large pot of boiling water for about 3 minutes or until limp.
Drain.
Combine egg, milk, onions, salt, pepper, beef and cooked rice.
Place about 1/4 cup meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Fold in sides and roll ends over meat.
Place in crock-pot.
Combine tomato sauce with brown sugar, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and cook 7 to 9 hours.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; add dry ingredients, then remaining ingredients.
Mixture will be a heavy dough.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
When done, leave in pan.
Pour Buttermilk Sauce over cake and let cool completely in pan.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Saute onions and garlic for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to spinach. Layer spinach on bottom of well-greased pan (9-inch pie plate). Spread layer of cottage cheese over mixture.
Repeat until all of spinach and cottage cheese is used up.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, lemon juice and pepper together until smooth.
Pour over spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add nutmeg (if desired). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a
x
x 2-inch pan.
Fill the bottom with pineapple and
pour
the
pie filling on top of it.
Don't mix them together.
Pour cake mix over the top and top with butter squares.
Bake at 350° for about a half hour or so.

title: kukunn
directions: Follow directions on bread roll box; let rise, then put raised dough in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Let rise again. Punch holes in it. Pour cream over top.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well in quart jar.
Mash eggs and cheese and add to mixture.

title: blackberry jelly - sugar-free
directions: In saucepan, soften gelatin in blackberry juice and lemon juice.
Bring to a rolling boil; continue to boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in the liquid sweetener.
Put in hot sterile jars and seal.
Grape juice may be used instead of blackberry juice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix in boiler the cornstarch, strawberry jello, sugar and boiling water; let cool.
Arrange the pint of berries in prepared and cooled crust.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Add Dream Whip before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut the tops off the pepper; clean first, then blanche green peppers in large pan of water.
Cook the rice as directed on box. Fry the bacon slices and crumble.
Brown hamburger meat in large skillet; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Then stir in the rice, bacon slices and add Worcestershire sauce to taste (2 tablespoons).

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl combine mayonnaise, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper; add to macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes and onions.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 6 cups.

title: loong poong salad
directions: Drain and combine all ingredients.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt bars in microwave or on top of stove; melt with syrup. Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Well-grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan and a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Fill Bundt pan just a little over 1/2 full; pour remainder in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pans.
Serve with hot fudge sauce and ice cream.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in hot milk.
Pour over cracker crumbs; mix well. Add squash, seasoning and beaten eggs.
Pour into baking dish and cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and let chill for about 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put cheese in the pot.
Put some milk in the pot, then the macaroni.
Stir the mixture.
When it's all done, you have something to eat.

title: mock lasagna casserole
directions: In skillet, brown the meat; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water, garlic salt, pepper and basil.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half each macaroni, cottage cheese, shredded cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in cake pan.
Mix egg whites, sugar and oleo.
Beat with mixer for 10 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Heat griddle to medium (340°).
In shallow bowl or pie pan, combine all ingredients except margarine and bread.
Mix well. Melt margarine on griddle.
Dip bread in egg mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Cook on griddle over medium heat about 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, orange slices and pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers.
Drain.
Add seasonings and water.
Stir and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until meat is well seasoned.
Place meat mixture in large stew pot with all other ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste!
Makes 3 quarts.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In pot, melt the chocolate morsels, margarine and milk.
In large bowl, mix the pecans and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture over nuts and marshmallows.
Mix quickly.
Put wax paper in bottom of pan.
Cool 2 hours.

title: minestrone with orzo
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Stir in water, undrained tomatoes and beef bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrot, sugar, basil and nutmeg. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.
Stir in zucchini, spinach and pasta.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more or until pasta is tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and crusty Italian bread, if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together first 3 items.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Put in 9 x 12-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In medium bowl toss meat cubes with flour to coat.
In Dutch oven brown meat in hot oil.
Add onion, paprika, salt, pepper and broth; mix well.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: mexican corn and cheese soup
directions: Cook and stir corn and garlic in margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Add all of the remaining ingredients, except chips.
Stir soup until heated thoroughly and the cheese is melted.
Top individual servings with tortilla chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts; remove chicken from bone.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Pour French dressing over chicken and marinate overnight.
The following day add celery and mayonnaise.
Place in a baking dish and cover with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle can of onions on top and bake for 5 additional minutes.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in oblong cake pan (13 x 9-inches) and put in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle crumbs over melted butter.
Mix together and then press with fork to form bottom layer. Drizzle condensed milk over graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and then coconut, then sprinkle chopped nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Let cool and cut into squares.
May be frozen.

title: bran muffin mix(large batch)
directions: Put All-Bran and Shredded Wheat in a bowl and pour 1/2 cup boiling water over it; let stand.
Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients (salt, baking powder, flour and baking soda).
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add buttermilk, moist cereal, dates and raisins.
Blend well. Fill desired amount of muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Excess batter will keep a few weeks or bake all muffins and freeze.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Grind the wafers or roll them into crumbs and put 1/2 of them in the bottom of your pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour this mixture over the crumbs.
Whip the whipping cream.
Add the pineapple and pour over the first mixture.
Cover with the rest of the crumbs and put in icebox overnight.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce, kidney beans, olives and cheese.
Layer ingredients starting with the hamburger, beans, etc.
Top with taco chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frank-green bean casserole
directions: Brown
franks
in
hot
fat
in
heavy skillet.
Remove franks.
Stir
flour
into remaining shortening, gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Blend in salt, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir in drained beans and potatoes, arrange
franks on top, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add applesauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple and celery.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan if you want to make squares for serving.
(Serving from the pan is made easier by oiling the pan first.)

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add spaghetti sauce with 2 tablespoons sugar to
hamburger.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add hamburger and spaghetti sauce with macaroni.
Mix Cheddar cheese with hamburger mixture. Bake in casserole dish at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Whip Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Cover pie crust with mixture.
Pour blueberry filling over the top. Refrigerate for several hours.
(May use any type of pie filling.)

title: oriental dipping sauce
directions: To Microwave:
In medium microwave-safe bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave on High 3 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring once during cooking. Serve with chicken nuggets, fish sticks, fried eggplant, zucchini sticks or onion rings.

title: caramel graham fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine 1 1/2 cups of the brownie mix, graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine; mix well.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: meat balls
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf florentine
directions: Mix ground beef, spinach, onion, egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley and half of the spaghetti sauce.
Pack meat loaf mixture into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat the remaining sauce and serve on cooked rice or spaghetti.

title: best homemade pizza
directions: Make pizza crust as directed on package.
Brown Italian sausage in skillet and drain.
When crust is ready, spread with greased hands onto a 12 x 18 x 1-inch well-greased cookie sheet. Mix together Ragu sauce and tomato sauce and spread on crust. Chop onion.
Slice olives.
Spread sausage on top of sauce.
Drop on onions, olives and mushrooms.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese first, then Parmesan cheese, enough to cover lightly.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until cheese starts to brown.

title: layered dessert
directions: In 9 X 13 pan, crumble angel food cake into bottom of pan. Pour prepared instant pudding over cake.
Slice bananas and layer over pudding and cake.
Slice strawberries and layer over bananas. Pour drained pineapple over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: shrimply divine(shrimp dip)
directions: Drain shrimp.
Rinse shrimp and drain again.
Mix all ingredients together and enjoy!

title: spinach ricotta (italian dumplings)
directions: Note:
The spinach can be cooked or frozen but chop, thaw and squeeze dry and Swiss chard may be substituted.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and vanilla flavoring.
Add eggs, oil, apples and nuts; mix well.
Grease tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan in about 5 or 10 minutes.

title: sour-cream cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda, flour, salt and sour cream; add to sugar and margarine mixture. Add flavoring and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 1 hour and 15 minutes, depending on oven.

title: selah's friendship cake
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly.
Add handshake and hugs separately.
Slowly stir in love.
Sift sympathy and hospitality. Fold in carefully.
Bake in a warm heart.
Serve real often, at least 3 times a week.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind apples, oranges (with rind), lemon and cranberries.
Mix with sugar and nuts; chill 2 hours.
Heat pineapple juice and pour over raspberry jello and unflavored gelatin.
Cool slightly. Pour jello mixture into fruit and pour into molds.

title: cocoa buttermilk cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together. Cream the butter with vanilla. Gradually add sugar. Cream well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Alternately add dry ingredients by fourths and buttermilk by thirds.
Beat only until blended after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with Chocolate Creamy Frosting.

title: original chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer ingredients in order and bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°. After 25 minutes, make slits in cake and continue baking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange.
Add sugar to taste.
Let stand while you chop celery.
Add celery and chopped nuts.
Mix orange jello with 3/4 cup water.
Let firm around edges while stirring once in a while.
When jello begins to firm, add mixture and chill until set.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add jello to 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Mix and add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Let jell and whip in cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and remaining ingredients.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Chill dough. Roll out and bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until turning brown.

title: black cherry punch
directions: Lemonade concentrate should be thawed and all other ingredients chilled.
Combine water, grenadine syrup and lemonade concentrate.
Add soda and carbonated water by slowly pouring down the side of the bowl or pitcher.
Add ice cubes or ice ring. Garnish each serving with a lime slice and a maraschino cherry on a cocktail server, if desired.
Makes
9 cups.

title: claudia's easy peach cobbler
directions: Grease 1-quart pan or dish.
Peel and slice peaches.
Place in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter.
Spoon in dry ingredients over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, milk and eggs, one at a time, beating after adding each egg.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Thaw lemonade; add 2 cans water.
Thaw orange juice; add 2 cans water.
Mix.
Dissolve Jell-O in one cup hot water, then add to juices.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Add sugar, salt and vanilla to egg.
Then add milk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream first 2
ingredients
together
until
light
and fluffy.
Sift next 4
together
and add alternately with other ingredients.
Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy in Proverbs 23:14.
Add next
ingredients,	fold in beaten egg yolks and stiffly beaten egg whites
carefully.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35	to
40	minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
ahead of needed time and refrigerate.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat and pour in unbaked frozen pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook hen in plenty of water.
Let stand overnight, refrigerated.
Cook the spaghetti in broth, then add the remaining ingredients.
Make White Sauce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Serve with raw vegetables.

title: mini tostados
directions: Fry ground beef with taco seasoning; drain fat.
Put taco meat on tortilla chip (individually).
Sprinkle cheese over the top. You can put jalapeno pepper slices and olive slices on each or just one or the other.
In oven, toast long enough for cheese to melt.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: red bean dip
directions: Wash and drain kidney beans well. Chill, then pat dry. Mix all remaining ingredients and add beans, mixing well.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Boil the tea bags in 1 c. of water for 2-3 minutes. Then add all ingredients together and stir well.
Put mixture in freezer. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage and meat one dish meal
directions: In an electric frypan, layer cabbage, onion, sliced potatoes and ground beef.
Top this with 1 large can of tomato sauce; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: the big monster cookies
directions: Mix really good.
Put 1 heaping tablespoonful on cookie sheet, 6 on a sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Real soft until cooled down, then take off sheet.
Place on wax paper to finish cooling.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn in crust.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Top with chilled pie filling just before serving.

title: icebox sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Shape into three 1-inch logs.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix.

title: omelet
directions: Cover 6 slices of bread with chopped ham or bacon, then put 6 slices Velveeta cheese and another 6 slices of bread on top of that.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt and pepper to suit taste. Pour over other ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes mixed with melted butter.
Is best to make and let set 6 to 8 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and set.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate squares in heavy saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Combine sugar and flour; stir into chocolate mixture.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Add salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan (buttered) and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Filling should still be moist.
Serve warm with whipped cream and cherries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Boil beans for 45 minutes or until tender and drain. Put in 4-quart crock-pot.
Put all other ingredients in a saucepan and heat until all is mixed and dissolved.
Pour into crock-pot.
Stir and cook overnight on low.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix sugar and butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in an airtight bowl in refrigerator.
Dough is better when thoroughly cold or made the night before use.
Grease muffin tins.
Spoon in dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: katie's truffle
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions. Fold Cool Whip into pudding. Layer in bowl pieces of cake, fruit, pudding, cake, fruit and pudding. You can top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: caesar salad and caesar dressing
directions: Rub the inside of the salad bowl with the garlic clove.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add to salad bowl.
Break egg onto lettuce and toss.
Add lemon juice and toss again.

title: souperburger
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion in oil; stir to separate. Add soup and seasonings.
Cook for 5 minutes; stir.
Serve on buns.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: golden corn and broccoli
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine broccoli and water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 8 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Stir occasionally; drain in colander.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in buttered casserole for 1 hour at 375°.

title: strawberry sour cream pie
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar.
Stir in sour cream, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust and chill about 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: vegetable drink
directions: Cook the celery, beets, carrots and onions separately until they are very soft.
Mash them very fine.
Strain and add the lemon juice and rind and tomato juice.
Add salt to taste, then put into jars and cook for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: walnut cream fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Stirring constantly, heat to boiling, and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: jan's artichoke spread
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients, except paprika.
Spoon into a small casserole dish which has been slightly greased. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake two tone bites
directions: Combine over hot, not boiling, water the butterscotch morsels, butter and water.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Add nuts; stir well.
Press into foil lined 8-inch square pan. Combine over hot, not boiling, water the semi-sweet morsels, corn syrup and water.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Pour chocolate mixture evenly over butterscotch layer.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: andrew's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large covered pot.
Mix well. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; partially cover and simmer very gently for 1 hour.
Add a bit
more water if sauce gets too thick.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.
Keeps well in covered glass jar in refrigerator for several months.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Mix together and bring to full boil.
Then keep boiling for 25 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: linguine and red peppers
directions: Combine olive oil, red peppers, carrots, pears, crushed tomatoes, basil and pepper.
Stir and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.
Pour sauce over cooked linguine and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with green salad and hot bread.

title: pumpkin bars(great!)
directions: Bring margarine and water to a boil in medium saucepan. Remove from heat.
Add flour and mix with wooden spoon until it makes a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix each one until it disappears.
Drop batter in shape of ring on lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
Turn off oven.
Leave in 10 minutes more.
Cool.
Slice top off, fill and top.

title: waffle corn bread
directions: Combine butter and
sugar; add eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Bake	from 3 to 5 minutes in hot waffle iron.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stephanie's coq au vin
directions: Brown chicken in butter and olive oil.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Brown bacon, adding onion and garlic.
Saute small onions in butter.
Add bouillon and water.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in butter and drain slightly.
Place chicken in two large cooking pots.
Pour 1/2 can chicken broth in each pot.
Add 1 cup of wine to each pot.
Add bacon, small onions and the broth they cooked in, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for company.
The taste improves with reheating.

title: fish cutlet
directions: In large mixing bowl, mash potato and slightly crush the onion and chili peppers into it.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Make small patties and deep fry both sides in oil.
It is ready to serve when both sides are golden brown.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Add the other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, then flour, soda and salt.
Last add mincemeat.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ed marks' family chicken tamales
directions: Bring water, chicken soup and bay leaves to a boil.
Add farina, cornmeal and chili powder, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Remove bay leaves when cooked.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook pasta until done, 10 to 12 minutes.
Rinse pasta.

title: pico de gallo
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, mix well and serve as an appetizer with nachos or along with sour cream and lettuce as an entree enhancement.
